du'),(233,'\'Mitti Di Khushboo Guitar Chords with Strum (w/wo Capo) - Abhijeet\'','\'Parting is always bittersweet and it is the memories that gnaw us from inside. Mitti di khushboo by the mellifluous Ayushmann Khurrana is the song that harmonises well with this feeling. This single has been composed by Rochak Kohli and written by Rochak Kohli, Gurpreet Saini, Gautam Govind Sharma. This melody uses the guitars, the piano and the drums very artfully. Mitti di khushboo chords are simple if they are played with a capo. The capo position is in the 2nd fret. The guitar chords of Mitti di khushboo are Em, C, D, Bm & A. The song has been played in the F#m scale with a signature 4/4 beat and a moderately paced tempo. Mitti di khushboo guitar chords have a smooth progression and have a strumming pattern that is D D UDUDU D. This melody was released years back but still has that fresh feeling in it and doesn’t fail to impress us till date.\n: D D UDUDU D\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: F#m\n: Required\n: 2nd Fret\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: Em, C, D, Bm, A\n\n\n: Easy with Capo\nJadon [Em] ambaran barasaya [C]paani\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[C]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo[Em]ayi…\n[C]Ambraan barasyaa[Em]paani…[Bm]…[D]\nChaliye[Em]chal muddiye[C]sajna\n\n[Em]Chal muddiye[Am]bandeya…[D]\n\n[Em]Chal muddiye us[C]raah\n\n[D]Jithe vasdi\n\n[C]Jithe vasdi\n\n[D]Jithe vasdi[Em]khudaayi\nJado [Em] ambara barasyaa [C]paani\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[C]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo [Em]ayi…\n:\n\n[Em] [C]\n[Em]Jahan jad oh kolsi\n\n[C]Naa kadar na mol si\n\n[A]Chad aye[Am]apne he[D]vehde\n\n[Em]Mulak paraye ne\n\n[C]Gharan de kiraaye ne\n\n[B]Ho lay[Am]apne si[D]jedde\noh kallaan [Em]labda firaan din[C]raat\n\n[Em]Labda firaan tera[Am]sath[D]\n[Em]Saiyaan karade [C]mulaakat\n\n[D]Jithe vasdi\n\n[C]Jithe vasdi\n\n[D]Jithe vasdi[Em]khudaayi\nJadon[Em]ambara barasiya[C]pani\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[C]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo[Em] aayi\n[Em]Jadon mere shehar’nu\n\n[C]Jandey dekhe gair’nu\n\n[A]Jandiyan si[Am]meri wi[B]sadawaan\n\n[Em]Betha kinni durr me\n\n[C]Hoke majburr me\n\n[B]Rabba teri [Am]kidda di[D]sajavaan\n[Em]Ikk sunle [C]awaaz\n\n[Em]Ikk puri karde meri [Am]aas[D]\n[Em]Ikk mann ja[C]ardaas\n\n[D]Otho na muddke\n\n[C]Otho na muddke\n\n[D]Otho na muddke[Em]bulaayi\nJadon[Em]ambaraan barasiya [C]paani\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[C]Mitti di khushboo\n\n[D]Mitti di khushboo [Em]aayi [Two Times]\n: Mitti di khushboo is a song that is very conversational and metaphorical. The lyrics are intensely heart rendering and very fondly sing about the memories that the dear beloved has left behind with the lover. The lyrics are in Punjabi and have that folk Sufi touch. The entire team has done an extremely commendable job by creating a soundtrack so beautiful and touching. The piano and the guitars together create a very doleful effect and the music is indeed very soothing. There is a pacifying feeling in this melody. The song has no fast and exciting beats and the rhythm flows on leisurely striking the inner chords of our hearts. Ayushmann Khurrana is beyond all praise and perfection as usual. His gentle and powerful voice captures that impact very gracefully and the intended emotions are presented to the audience enchantingly. That is why we are forced to come back to this melody again and again. Filmed on Ayushmann himself and the phenomenal Huma, the video of this song is a treat to the eyes. This song is perfect for every crestfallen lover who is suffering from a painful separation. And if you want to express your grief through music, strum these chords on your guitar and let music speak for you.\n: Mitti Di Khushboo\n\n\n: Ayushmann Khurrana\n\n\n: Rochak Kohli\n\n\n Rochak Kohli, Gautam Sharma & Gurpreet Saini\n\n\n: T-Series\n\n\n: Punjabi\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: October 2014\n\n\n: Rainy Day Song\'','\'New\'','Mitti-Di-Khushboo-Guitar-Chords-with-Strum--w-wo-Capo----Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(234,'\'Easy - Guitar: Nanhi Pari Chords by Sonu Nigam (Asifa) - Abhijeet\'','\'We worship women, raise her to the altar and speak about their empowerment, but do we treat them right? Do we protect them? Do we care for them? Nanhi pari from Express Yourself is a song that talks about the little angel Asifa who was a victim of the atrocity men commit on women. Sung, penned down and composed by the evergreen Sonu Nigam himself, this soulful melody is from the feature film soundtrack genre. The track uses the guitars, bass guitar and flutes brilliantly. Nanhi pari chords are easy and simple. The guitar chords of Nanhi pari are six in number and they are Em, C, D, Am, F#, A. The song has a signature 4/4 beat with a moderately paced tempo. This track has been played in the Em scale. The chords of Nanhi pari have a very smooth and harmonious progression. This number is intensely heart rendering and touching.\n: 102\n\n\n: Em\n\n\n: 4/4\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: Em, C, D, Am, F#, A\n\n\n: Easy\n:\n\n[Em]\n[Em]Choti si ik nanhi pari[C]Kashmir [D]me\n\n[Em]Likh ke kya ayi thi wo[C]takdeer [D]me[C]\n[Em]Choti si ik nanhi pari[C]Kashmir [D]me\n\n[Em]Likh ke kya ayi thi wo[C]takdeer [Em]me\n[Em]Khoyi thi wo guddiyo [C]ki taabir[D]me\n\n[Em]Fas gyi par [C]jallaado ki bheed[Em]me\nWo[E]tadapti rhi or wo[Am] haste rhe\n\n[E]Zulam ke faans me usko [C]kaste rhe\n\n[B]Bewajaah!\n[Em]Oh[B] ho… [D]Kahan kho gyi tu [B]Asifa\n\n[Em]Oh[B] ho… [D]Kya Jindagi thi [B]Asifa\n:\n\n[Em] [Am] [G] [Am] [B]\n[Em]Choti si ek nanhi pari [C]Kashmir [D]me\n\n[Em]Likh ke kya ayi thi wo [C]takdeer [D]me[C]\n[Em]Kya un darindo[F#] ki\n\nThi [C]nhi koi [B]hum jesi[Em]maa\n\n[Em]Kissne sikhaaya [F#]unhein\n\nKitni[C]anmol [B]hoti[Em] hai jaan\nItni[A]nafrat ko kaise[G]paale hai\n\nAye[A] Khuda tera adam[B] bta\n[Em]Oh [B] ho… [D]Kahan kho gayi tu[B]Asifa\n\n[Em]Oh [B] ho… [D]Kya zindagi thi[B]Asifa\n:\n\n[Em] [D] [C] [B]\n