g by the mellifluous Mohit Chauhan and Suzanne D’ Mello, the song has been composed by the true legend A. R. Rahman and penned by the poetic Irshad Kamil. This track is from the feature film soundtrack genre and uses the piano and the guitar and drums at the background. Tum ho chords are easy if played on the guitar with the capo. The position of the capo is on the 5th fret. The guitar chords of Tum ho are Am, Em, C, F, G & Dm. The tempo is moderately paced and the beat is 4/4. The chords of Tum ho have a smooth progression and a strumming pattern of DDD UDUDD DU. This track has been played in the F scale.\n: DDD UDUDD DU\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Accurate & Verified by Team\n\n\n: F\n\n\n: 6\n: Am, Em, C, F, G, Dm\n: 5th Fret\n: DDD UDUDD DU\n[Am]Hmmm..[Em]oh…\n\n[C]ooh….[G]ho…\n\n[Am]Hmm…[Em]ooh\n\nTum[F]ho..[G]….\nTum [C] ho [F] pass mere\n\n[C] sath mere ho[Em]tum yoon..[E]\n\n[F]Jitna mehsoos [C]karu tum ko\n\n[Dm]utna he paa bhi[G]lu\n:\n\n[C]hm..[F]\nTum [C]ho[F]mere liye\n\n[C]mere liye ho[Em]tum yu..[E]\n\nKhud[F]ko me haar[C]gya tumko\n\n[Dm]Tumko me jeeta [G]hoon\n:\n\n[Am]Hmm..[Em]oO…[C]Oo…[G]ho…\n\n[Am]Hmm..[Em]oO…Tum [F] ho…[G]\n[C]Hmmm…[Em]hmmm…[Am]ahaan…[F]haa…\nKahi [C]se kahi [Em]ko… [D] bhi\n\nAayo [G]bewajah[C]chale\n\nPuche [D]bina kisi[G]se hum [C]mile\n:\n\n[Am]…[Em]\n[Am]Bandeehshein na[F]rhi\n\n[B]Koi [Em]baaki…[F]tum ho…[C]\nTum [C]ho [F]paas mere\n\n[C]sath mere ho[Em]tum yu…[E]\n\n[F]Jitna mehsus[C]karu tumko\n\n[Dm]utna he paa bhi [G]lu\n[Am]Hmmm..[Em]oh…\n\n[C]ooh….[G]ho…\n\n[Am]Hmm…[Em]ooh\n\nTum[F]ho..[G]….\n: Tum ho is an intensely romantic number. It is indeed one of the most popular romantic songs and one of the best love songs composed by Bollywood. Rahman is maestro undoubtedly and his genius is visible in this track. Tum ho focuses more on the vocals than the instruments , so there is a soft mellow music that plays in the background. The song drops its rhythm in the end where it slows down with no musical instrument at the back but the guitar and the piano to create a dramatic impact. Mohit Chauhan is brilliant and his extremely powerful vocals steal the show. His classical overtunes are mesmerising. Suzanne is stellar with her aria and she lends an opera feel to this amorous track. Her voice is immensely sweet and her humming and crooning keep us hooked to this melody. The lyrics are filled with love and passion in every bit and the charms and the magic of the beloved has been carved well in this number. Filmed on Nargis and the talented Ranbir Kapoor, the video of this song is just a treat to the eyes. This song is perfect for a candlelight romantic dinner or a slow ball dance with your lover serenading in your arms. And if you want to make her go all crazy for you and fall madly in love with you then play this melody to her and see how she falls head over heels in love with you.\n: Tum Ho Paas Mere\n\n\n: Rockstar\n\n\n: Mohit Chauhan & Kavita Krishnamurthy\n\n\n: T-Series\n\n\n: A.R. Rahman\n\n\n Irshad Kamil\n\n\n: 2011\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\'','\'New\'','Easy--Tum-Ho-Guitar-Chords-with-Strumming--w-wo-Capo----Rockstar---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(238,'\'[Easy] Kabir Singh: Mere Sohneya Guitar Chords with Strumming Pattern - Abhijeet\'','\'Love is a bliss, and the beloved is always beyond perfect. That sweet feeling which you get when you see your beloved has been well carved into words in this melody- Mere Sohneya from Kabir Singh. This track has been sung by Sachet Tandon and Parampara Thakur, composed by Sachet and Parampara and penned by Irshad Kamil. Mere Sohneya chords are simple and easy and can be picked up the amateurs and the beginners in a jiffy. Mere Sohneya is a guitar based song with a signature 4/4 beat and moderately paced tempo and uses acoustic guitars mainly and shehnai in the ending. The guitar chords of Mere Sohneya are A, E, D and the scale in which this song is played is A. The strumming pattern is D UUD UUD or D UDUD UDUD. This melody is very romantic and heart warming and celebrates the feeling of love in a melodious manner. This song is definitely going to be one of the top romantic love songs of this year.\n: D UUD UUD or D UDUD UDUD\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Accurate & Verified by Team\n: A\n\n\n: 3\n\n\n: A, E, D\n\n\n: D UUD UUD or D UDUD UDUD\n:\n\n[A] [D]\n[A]Banthanke mutiyaara aaiyaan\n\n[D]Aaiya patola banke\n\n[A]Kanna dey vich peeppal Patiyaan\n\n[D]Baanhi Chudaa khanke\n[A]Banthanke mutiyaara aaiyaan\n\n[D]Aaiya patola banke\n\n[A]Kanna dey vich peeppal patiyaan\n\n[D]Baanhi chudaa khanke\nMere [D]sohneya-sohneya [E]vey\n\nVe maahi mera [A]kitthe naio dil lagna\n\nMere [D]sohneya-sohneya [E]vey\n\nVe maahi mera [A]kitthe naio dil lagna\nHaye tera [A]rasta vey\nNange pair [D]turna vey\n\nTu hai [A]nal mere\n\nTa me kyu aye [E]darna vey\nTera [A]raasta vey\n\nNangye pair [D]turna vey\n\nTu hai [A]naal Mere\n\nTa me kyu aey [E]darna vey\nHaaye [D]dono ne rona… [E]dono ne hasna\n\n[D]Sabnu hai dassna[E]aa [A]aa\nMere[D] sohneya soneya [E] ve\n\nVe maahi mera [A]kithe nahiyo dil lagna\n\nMere[D] sohneya soneya [E] ve\n\nVe maahi mera [A]kithe nahiyo dil lagna\n[A]Ve maahi mera [A]kithe nahiyo dil\n\nlag[E]naa…\n\n[A]Ve maahi mera [A]kitthe nahiyo dil\n\nlag[E]naa..\n[A]Banthanke mutiyaara aaiyaan\n\n[D]Aaiyaan patola banke\n\n[A]Kanna dey vich peeppal patiyaan\n\n[D]Baanhi chudaa khanke\n: Mere Sohneya is a soundtrack filled with the hues and tinge of passion in every bit of it. The lyrics have been written in Punjabi and have a very Sufi feel. The song acknowledges the beauty and the charms of the beloved and how the love struck lover can not take his mind off his lady love. Irshad Kamil has magic in his pen as he artfully expresses our thoughts and emotions in this lovely song. The music is very soothing and has no fast or exciting beats. It has a smooth flow of rhythm. The guitars are very euphonious and produce a dulcet music. The singers have done a commendable job. Sachet has a gentle and pacifying voice while Parampara has low scaled powerful vocals which are truly harmonious to the ears. The song has been filmed on the handsome Shahid Kapoor and the pretty Kiara Advani and their chemistry on screen is intensely sizzling. The melody is perfect for a romantic date night or a quiet evening with your lover serenading in your arms. And well if you want to walk the extra mile and surprise your beloved then strum the chords of Mere Sohneya on your guitar and make her blush and go all gaga over you.\n: Mere Sohneya\n\n\n: Sachet Tandon & Parampara Thakur\n\n\n: Kabir Singh\n\n\n: Irshad Kamil\n\n\n: Sachet-Parampara\n\n\n: 2019\'','\'New\'','-Easy--Kabir-Singh--Mere-Sohneya-Guitar-Chords-with-Strumming-Pattern---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(239,'\'Kidnap - Guitar: Ektu Jayga Dena Chords with Strumming Pattern - Abhijeet\'','\'Ektu jayega dena is a very peppy and bubbly song that will make you run to the dance floor and groove with your better half. The melody is from the film Kidnap, and has been sung by the mellifluous Armaan Malik, composed by the maestro Jeet Gannguli and penned down by the poetic Ritam Sen. This song is from the feature film soundtrack genre and uses the guitars, the drums and several other instruments euphoniously. Ektu jayga dena chords are simple and can be played by the beginner with ease. The guitar chords of Ektu jayga dena are five in number and they are Am, G, F, Em, & C. The chords of Ektu jayga dena have a harmonious progression and follow a strumming pattern of D UD D. This track has been played in the Am scale with a signature 4/4 beat and a moderately paced tempo.\n: Am\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: Am, G, F, Em, & C\n\n\n: D UD D\n(Am) Ektu jayga dena (F)\n\nAmay(C)ektu jaayga dena\n\n(G)Jeno torr a(Em)ador makhte(F)pari\n(Am)Ektu jayga dena\n\nAmay(C) ektu jayga dena\n\n(G)Jeno(Em)torr khoborr rakhte(F)pari\n\nJeno(Em)tor khobor rakhte(F)paari\n(Am)Toke niye(G)kije kori buj(F)hina\n\n(Am)Toke chara(G)keno kichhu khuj(Am)jina\n(Am)Mone mone tor(F)nesha nesha ghor\n\nPhire-fhire toke(E)chawa\n\n(Am)Kachha-kachhi thak, chokhe(F)chokhe daak\n\n(G)Elo melo dikk(Am)hawa\nMone mone tor(F)nesha nesha ghor\n\n(E)Phire phire toke(G)chawa\n\n(Am)Kachha kachhi thak, (F)chokhe chokhe daak\n\nElo melo(G)dikk(Am)hawa\nEktu jayga(G)dena\n\nAmay(F) ektu jayga dena\n\nJeno(Em) tor pashe hant tey(F) paari\n\nJeno(Em) tor sathe banchtey(F) paari\n(Am)Kaana-kaani hokk, Jana jani(F) hokk\n\nChuppi-chuppi (Em)kachhe (G)jawwa\n\n(Am)Hasi-hasi mukh, luko(F)churi sukh\n\nBhaalobeshe(G)kachhe pawwa\n(Am)Kaana kaani hok, jaana(F)jaani hokk\n\n(Em)Chuppi chuppi kache(G) jawwa\n\n(Am)Hasi-hasi mukh, luko(F) churi sukh\n\n(G)Bhaalobeshe kache paw(Am)aa\nEktu jayga(G) dena\n\nAmay(F) ektu jayga (G)dena\n\nJeno tor(Em) aador makhtey(F)paari\n(Am)Ektu jayga dena\n\nAmay(C)ektu jayga dena\n\nJeno(Em)tor khobor rakhte(F)paari\n\nJeno(Em)tor khobor (F)rakhte (C)paari(Am)\n: Ektu jayga dena is one of the most popular romantic songs composed by the Bengali film industry. The song has a different groovy feel and you are forced to sway to this rocking tune and tap your feet to the beats. The music is very jovial and creates a very cheerful and romantic mood. The lyrics are quite lovey dovey and every love struck couple can find themselves relating to this number and smiling without any reason. Jeet Gannguli has done a commendable job along with his entire crew and has gifted us with another fine composition. Armaan Malik is as usual stellar and his gentle and soothing vocals compel us to come back to this song again and again. Filmed on the handsome Dev and the beautiful Rukmini, their on screen chemistry is just a delight to watch. This track is perfect for a romantic date where you can serenade with your lover in your arms, or just do a small jig with your lady love on the dance floor. And like Dev, if you want to dedicate a song to someone special, then search no further cause this is just the melody that you are looking for.\n: Ektu Jayga Dena\n\n\n: Armaan Malik\n\n\n: Jeet Ganguli\n\n\n Ritam Sen\n\n\n: Kidnap\n\n\n: 2019\n\n\n: Surinder Films\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Bangla (Bengali)\'','\'New\'','Kidnap---Guitar--Ektu-Jayga-Dena-Chords-with-Strumming-Pattern---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(240,'\'Arijit Singh: Bandeya Guitar Chords with Strumming | Dil Junglee - Abhijeet\'','\'Bandeya is a song that is quite heart warming and heart rendering. From the movie Dil Junglee, this song is a plea to the beloved to go to some place unknown where they wont be recognized. Sung by the king of sad songs Arijit Singh, this song has been composed by the ingenious duo Sharib and Toshi, and penned by the poetic Dr. Devendra Kafir. This melody is from the feature film soundtrack genre and uses the guitar and other string instruments mellifluously. Bandeya chords are simple and can be played by the amateurs with ease. The guitar chords of Bandeya are G, Em, D, C, & Bm. This song has a moderately paced tempo, a signature 4/4 beat and the progression of the chords of Bandeya is very smooth and harmonious with a strumming pattern of DUDU DUDU or D U (C) D DDDU. The key scale in which this melody has been played is G.\n: DUDU DUDU or D U (C) D DDDU\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Accuracy & Verified by Team\n: G Major\n\n\n: 4/4\n\n\n: 91\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: G, Em, D, C, & Bm\n\n\n: DUDU DUDU or D U (C) D DDDU\n:\n |——-7—10-8-7-8———7—-\n\n\n |–10——————–10——–\n\n\n |————————————\n\n\n |————————————\n |—————–7——————\n\n\n |–8-10—7-8——-10-8-10——\n\n\n |————————————\n\n\n |————————————\n:\n\n[G] [Em] [D]\n[G]Chal, chal ve tu bandeya [Em]uss galiye\n\nJahaan [D]koi kisi ko na jaane\n:\n\n[G] [Em] [D]\n[G]Chal, chal ve tu bandeya [Em]uss galiye\n\nJahaan [D]koi kisi ko na jaane\n\nKya [G]rehna wahaan par [Em]sun bandeya\n\nJahaan [D]apne hi na pehchaane\nReh [G]gaye hain jo tujhme\n\nMere [D]lamhe lauta de\n\nMeri [Em]aankhon mein [G]aake\n\nMujhe [D]thoda rula [G]de\n[G]Chal, chal ve tu bandeya [Em]uss galiye\n\nJahaan [D]koi kisi ko na jaane, hmm\n:\n\n[G] [Em] [D]\n\n[G] [Em] [D]\n[G]Khwab jo huey hain khandar\n\n[Em]Khwab hi nahi thhe\n\nIk [C]neend thi neem [D]si… haaye\n\n[Bm]Kho diya hai tune jisko\n\n[Em]Tera hi nahi tha\n\nIk [C]haar thi [D]jeet si…\n[D]Kitna rulayega [Em]ye toh bata\n\nRabba ve tujhe hai tere rab da waasta\nChal, chal ve tu bandeya uss galiye\n\nJahaan[D] koi kisi ko na jaane\n\nKya [G]rehna wahaan par[Em] sun bandeya\n\nJahaan[D] apne hi na pehchaane…\n[G]Hmm…!\n: Bandeya is a song with a Punjabi feel and has a very folk feeling about it. The lyrics talk about a wistful love and very beautifully express an emotion which is indescribable. Kafir has magically penned down all the thoughts we experience when we are having a tumultuous relation with our beloved. The music is quite soothing and soft and one can feel that note of sadness in the mellow tune. Arijit Singh needs no further praise as his crooning is beyond perfection. His powerful and velvety smooth vocals indeed compel us to listen to this track on the repeat mode. Bandeya is a very emotional song that is immensely addictive and pacifying. It harmonises well with the pensive rainy afternoon mood when you are one with solitude reminiscing those happy times you spent with your beloved. Filmed on the lovely Tapsee Pannu and the charming Saqib Saleem, their on screen chemistry is very mesmerising. This track is perfect for all the jilted lovers and for those who are having a tiff with their lovers. And if you want to make up for the fight and apologise to your better half, then play this song on your guitar and see how the quarrels become history and how love reigns.\n: Chal Ve Tu Bandeya Us Galiye\n\n\n: Arijit Singh\n\n\n: Dil Junglee\n\n\n: 2018\n\n\n Dr. Davendra Kafir\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Sony Music India\'','\'New\'','Arijit-Singh--Bandeya-Guitar-Chords-with-Strumming---Dil-Junglee---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(241,'\'[Easy] Bajrangi Bhaijaan: Tu Jo Mila Guitar Chords with Strumming Pattern - Abhijeet\'','\'Tu jo mila is a very beautiful song that is filled with love, compassion and emotions of a different kind. From the super hit film Bajrangi Bhaijaan, this melody has been sung by the mellifluous K.K., composed by the maestro Pritam and penned by Kausar Munir. This track hails from the feature film soundtrack genre and uses guitars and other string instruments brilliantly. Tu jo mila chords are easy and simple and can be played by the amateurs effortlessly. There is a harmonious progression of the chords of Tu jo mila and the number has a moderately paced tempo and a signature 4/4 beat. The guitar chords of Tu jo mila are C, Em, Am, G, F & Dm. This melody has been played in the C scale and the strumming pattern of the chords are D DD DDD or D UDUD UDUD. This song is a heart warming number which is quite addictive and will make you listen to it on loop.\n: D DD DDD or D UDUD UDUD\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Accurate & Verified by Team\n: C\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: Not Required\n\n\n: Easy\n\n\n: C, Em, Am, G, F, Dm\n: D DD DDD or D UDUD UDUD\n:\n[C]Aashiyana [Em]mera\n\n[C]Sath tere [Em/G]hai na\n\n[Am]Dhundtey [F]teri gali\n\n[F]Mujhko ghar [G] mila\n[C]Aaboodana [Em]mera\n\n[C]Hath tere [Em/G]hai na\n\n[Am]Dhundtey [F]tera Khuda\n\n[F]Mujhko Rab [G]mila\nTu Jo [Dm] mila\n\nLo ho gya me [G] Kaabil\n\nTu jo [C] mila\n\nTo ho gya sb [F] haasil…[C]haa\nMushkil [Dm]sahi\n\nAasaan hui [G]manzill\n\nKyun ki [F]Tu…[C]Dhad…[G]kan\n\nMe [C]Dil\n:\n\n[F] [C] [F]\n[C]Ruth jana [E