 this version has been used in the film Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana. This version is also heart wrenching and quite moving. Due credit must be given to the entire team who have worked hard to gift us this gem of a song. This song will help you to let out your angst and heal from the traumatic situation if you have been badly betrayed or left by your beloved and you find yourself submerged in pitiful tears, sorrow and the memories of the bygone lover. And if you want to give shape to your anguish, strum the chords on your guitar and let music heal your despairing soul.\'','\'New\'','Royee-Jande-Naina-Guitar-Chords---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(245,'\'Kabira Guitar Chords from Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani - Abhijeet\'','\'There are some songs that will always remain evergreen. Whatever it may be but these songs are like old wine- that become fresh and better with time. Kabira from Yeh Jawani Hai Deewani is that song. Performed by the mesmerizing Rekha Bhardwaj and the mellifluous Tochi Raina, this number has been composed by the maestro Pritam himself and penned by the poetic Amitabh Bhattacharya. The song hails from the pop and the Sufi genre, and has a very soulful tune with a signature 4/4 beat and a moderately paced tempo. The melody very beautifully uses the different guitars, the drums and other percussion instruments to create this wonderful symphony. The chords on the guitar are simple and the beginners can strum them easily. The harmonious progression of the chords and that feet tapping beat with the serenading tune is indeed pleasant to the ears.\n: DD UDUD DUDU\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Verified by Team\n\n\n: G\n: Not Required\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: G, D, A, Bm\n\n\n\nKaisi teri [G]khud garzi\n\nNa [D]dhoonp chunne na chaanv\n\nKaisi teri [G]khud garzi\n\nKisi [D]thorr tikke na paanv\nPlay the above paragaph twice\nStart strumming from here: DD UDUD 