 Mere Mehboob from Mr. X in Bombay. Sung by the one and only Kishore Kumar, this track has been composed by the creative genius Laxmikant-Pyarelal and penned by the poetic Anand Bakshi. This melody uses the percussions, the flutes, the violins and the guitars to create that mesmerising music. The chords on the guitar are simple and easy with a harmonious progression, so the beginners and the novice players can pick them effortlessly. This soundtrack is from the filmy soundtrack genre with a moderately paced tempo and a signature 4/4 beat. An intensely heart rendering number, this song is a gem indeed.\n: D UUD UUD\n\n\n: D D UUD DDU or D UD D UD\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: G#m\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: Optional\n\n\n: G#m, F#, E, & C#m\n\n\n: D UUD UUD or D D UUD DDU or D UD D UD\nMere (G#m)Mehboob Qaya(F#)mat Hogi\n\nAj Rus(E)waa Teri Galli(F#)yon Mein Moha(G#m)bbat Hogi\n\nMeri Nazr(G#m)ein To Gila(F#)Krti Hai\n\nTere Dil(E) Ko Bhi Sanam(F#)Tujh Se Shikaa(G#m)yat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(G#m)oob…\n(G#m)Teri Gali Mein (C#m) Ata Sanam\n\n(G#m)Nagmaan Waffa Ka (C#m) Gata Sanam\n\n(G#m)Tujhse Suna Na (C#m) Jata Sanam\n\nFir (G#m) Aaj(F#)Idhar Aa(E)ya Hu Magar Ye(F#)Khne Me Deew(E)aana\n\nKhatam Bs (G#m)Aaj Ye weh(F#)shatt Hogi\n\nAaj Rus(E)wa Teri Galli(F#)yon Me Moha(G#m)bbat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(G#m)oob…\n(G#m)Meri Tarah Tu(C#m)Aahein Bhare\n\n(G#m)Tu Bhi Kisise (C#m)Pyaar Kare\n\n(G#m)Or Rahe Wo(C#m)Tujhse Pare\n\nTu(G#m)ne Oh (F#)Sanam Dhaa(E)yein Hai Sitam To (F#)Ye Tu Bhul Na(E)Jaana\n\nKi Na Tujh(G#m)pe Bhi Inaa(F#)yat Hogi\n\nAaj Rus(E)wa Teri Gali(F#)yon Mein Mohab(G#m)bat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(G#m)oob…\nMere (G#m)Mehboob Qaya(F#)mat Hogi\n\nAj Rus(E)waa Teri Galli(F#)yon Mein Moha(G#m)bbat Hogi\n\nMeri Nazr(G#m)ein To Gila(F#)Krti Hai\n\nTere Dil(E) Ko Bhi Sanam(F#)Tujh Se Shikaa(G#m)yat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(G#m)oob…\n: \n: 4th Fret\n\n\n: Am, Em, D, C\n\n\n: C#m -> Am, G#m -> Em, F# -> D, E -> C\nMere (Em)Mehboob Qaya(D)mat Hogi\n\nAj Rus(C)waa Teri Galli(D)yon Mein Moha(Em)bbat Hogi\n\nMeri Nazr(Em)ein To Gila(D)Krti Hai\n\nTere Dil(C) Ko Bhi Sanam(D)Tujh Se Shikaa(Em)yat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(Em)oob…\n(Em)Teri Gali Mein (Am) Ata Sanam\n\n(Em)Nagmaan Waffa Ka (Am) Gata Sanam\n\n(Em)Tujhse Suna Na (Am) Jata Sanam\n\nFir (Em) Aaj(D)Idhar Aa(C)ya Hu Magar Ye(D)Khne Me Deew(C)aana\n\nKhatam Bs (Em)Aaj Ye weh(D)shatt Hogi\n\nAaj Rus(C)wa Teri Galli(D)yon Me Moha(Em)bbat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(Em)oob…\n(Em)Meri Tarah Tu(Am)Aahein Bhare\n\n(Em)Tu Bhi Kisise (Am)Pyaar Kare\n\n(Em)Or Rahe Wo(Am)Tujhse Pare\n\nTu(Em)ne Oh (D)Sanam Dhaa(C)yein Hai Sitam To (D)Ye Tu Bhul Na(C)Jaana\n\nKi Na Tujh(Em)pe Bhi Inaa(D)yat Hogi\n\nAaj Rus(C)wa Teri Gali(D)yon Mein Mohab(Em)bat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(Em)oob…\nMere (Em)Mehboob Qaya(D)mat Hogi\n\nAj Rus(C)waa Teri Galli(D)yon Mein Moha(Em)bbat Hogi\n\nMeri Nazr(Em)ein To Gila(D)Krti Hai\n\nTere Dil(C) Ko Bhi Sanam(D)Tujh Se Shikaa(Em)yat Hogi\n\nMere Mehb(Em)oob…\n: This melody has a profound sense of pathos infused in it. The song has some crests and troughs in the interlude, as the rhythm drops the tempo and again picks it up in the verses. This makes the song intensely endearing to the audience. Laxmikant-Pyarelal is the only duo who could have done such a commendable job. The lyrics are very conversational and heart touching. The song very effectively captures that ‘Abhimaan’ of the jilted lover and every rejected and heartbroken lovelorn lover can relate to this track. The song has a very doleful and morose feel and that makes it very harmonising to the pensive and crestfallen mood. That is why one keeps on coming back to this number. Kishore Kumar needs no praise as he is someone who will always remain unparalled. His extremely dulcet and powerful vocals are as usual enchanting and that is what makes this song unforgettable.\n: Kishore Kumar\n\n\n: Mr. X in Bombay\n\n\n Anand Bakshi\n\n\n: Laxmikant-Pyarelal\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Saregama\n\n\n: 1964\n: Mere Mehboob is an evergreen rendition that will never age. It will forever enthral us and all the upcoming future generations. This song is one of the best songs sung by Kishore Da. This number has been filmed on him and the beautiful actress Kumkum and the video though a black and white one speaks of a very colourful and emotional story. Since the video has been picturised on Kishor Da only he could feel the pain and the emotions of the character he was portraying and that is why the song has that wistful emotion that the character faces and nobody could have sung it better than him. This song has a lot of covers and reprised versions made years later, and two of them have been made by Sanam Puri and Honey Singh. This song is just ideal for someone who is facing the agonies of a separation or who has been badly betrayed and ditched by the beloved without any apparent reason. So if you are one of those suffering from any such similar situations, let your grief take the form of music and let those guitar chords that you strum speak for your woes and miseries to the world outside.\'','\'New\'','EASY--Mere-Mehboob-Qayamat-Hogi-Guitar-Chords-with-Strumming---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(271,'\'Guitar: Mon Aamar Chords by Arko | Shesh Theke Shuru - Abhijeet\'','\'| This is a 4 Chord song, the chords that we have used are A, D, E and F#m. We suggest you to play the song chords with D D UDUD D as the strumming pattern while the other pattern that we have for you is D UDUD UDUD where D is Down Stroke and U is Up Stroke and the song has BPM of 100.\nThe feeling of falling in love and that fresh new charming emotion is something that we always cherish for life, and Mon Amar from Shesh theke Shuru is that serenading track that justifies this statement. Sung and composed by the brilliant Arko, this track has been penned by the poetic Pranjol. This guitar based number uses the drums, the violins and the piano at the background melodiously. The tempo is moderately paced with a signature 4/4 beat. This song is from the filmi soundtrack genre and the smooth flowing rhythm and the feet tapping beats are mesmerising. The guitar chords are very simple and the novice player can pick them in a jiffy. The progression of the chords is harmonious and subtle and this song is indeed a soulful rendition.\n: D D UDUD D\n\n\n: D UDUD UDUD\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Verified by Team\n: A\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: A, D, E and F#m\n\n\n: 100\n\n\n: D D UDUD D or D UDUD UDUD\n(A)Mon vebeche amar… hobi\n\n(F#m)Mon ekeche moner cho(D)bi\n\n(A)Mon vebeche amar… hobi\n\nMon ekeche moner ch(D)obi\n(A)Kon hawa tey, kuaasha kete (D)jaaye\n\n(A)Tui daariye, ei shohor hete (D)jaaye\n(A)Mon amar oh Mon amar\n\nEyi (D)mon amar\n\nKhoje (A)jotno tor\n\nShopne bibhor du(D)noyon amar\n(A)Mon amar oh Mon amar\n\nEyi (D)mon amar\n\nKhoje (A)jotno tor\n\nShopne bibhor du(D)noyon amar\n(A)Mon vebeche amar… hobi\n\nMon ekeche (D)moner chobi\n\n(A)Mon vebeche amar… hobi\n\nMon ekeche moner cho(D)bi\n(A)Shob kichhu roilo tori hate\n\n(F#m)Tor pichu nei jonaaki raate\n(A)Tor kichhu jaaye ashe na taate\n\n(D)Bujhbi bol, kobe bujhbi bol?\n\n(A)Tori haasir golpo baje kane\n\n(F#m)Fhire ashi mugdho se uj(D)ane(A)\n\nBaan vashi ra bhaste thaka jaane\n\n(D)Khujbi chol, aalo khujbi chol (E)\n(A)Mon amar o Mon amar\n\nEi (D)mon amar\n\nKhoje (A)jotno tor\n\nShopne bibhor du (D)noyon amar\n(E) Ha (A)Mon amar o Mon amar\n\nEi (D)monn amar\n\nKhoje (A)jotno tor\n\nShopne bibhor du (D)noyon amar\n(A)O… oh… ho…\n(A)Mon vebeche amaar… hobi\n\n(D)Mon ekeche moner… chobi\n\n(A)Mon vebeche amaar… hobi\n\n(D)Mon ekeche moner… chobi\n: Mon Amar\n\n\n: Arko, Pravo Mukherjee\n\n\n: Arko\n\n\n Pranjol\n\n\n: Shesh Theke Shuru\n\n\n: Jet & Koel\n\n\n: Bangla (Bengali)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: April 2019\n\n\n: Grassroot Entertainment\n: Arko is a creative genius and is extremely talented. With the use of just few instruments and no heavy or exciting beats he has given us a very gentle and soothing track that is quite pleasant to the ears. The song has a very fascinating sensation about it. The lyrics are conversational and poetic. Pranjol has done a commendable job in carving and giving shape to those inexpressible feeling buried deep inside our hearts. The song talks about how the mind of the restless lover goes on searching for the beloved walking down the streets of his city and how she rests in his eyes. The song is about the feelings of a one sided lover and it has been beautifully conveyed through this melody. Arko has very gentle and velvety smooth vocals that make this track very heartfelt and heart- warming. His voice is mesmerising and attracts the listeners to listen to this song repeatedly on loop.\'','\'New\'','Guitar--Mon-Aamar-Chords-by-Arko---Shesh-Theke-Shuru---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(272,'\'Ishqe Di Chashni Guitar Chords - Strum | Bharat - Salman Khan - Abhijeet\'','\'Hello! So yeah we have the chords of a song that released today from Sallu bhai’s Bharat movie – \n. The chords that we have used in the song are a bit hard for beginners so we have also shared the overview with capo too. The chords without the capo are F#, G#, D#m, B & C# where F# is the key of the song and the chords with capo on the first fret are F, G, Dm, A#, & C.\nLove is the feeling that adds the various beautiful colours to our monotonous lives. It is like a sweetmeat that gives us happiness and fulfils our cravings. And Ishqe di Chashn from Bharat is that wonderful song which justifies this claim. Sung by the mellifluent Vishal and Shekhar featuring Abhijeet Srivastava, the melody was penned by the poetic Irshad Kamil and was composed by the maestros Vishal and Shekhar. With the acoustic guitars and esraj, this talented duo has created this mesmerising melody. The guitar chords are a bit intricate and the beginner will find it a little difficult to pick up the chords. Thus the capo is needed for all the novice players. The progression of the chords is smooth and harmonious and the piece is played on the F scale predominantly. The song has a moderately paced tempo with signature 4/4 beats and a very soothing rhythm.\n: D UDUD (c)\n\n\n: D UDUD UDUD or D UUD UUD\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: F#\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: 1st Fret\n\n\n: F, G, Dm, A#, C\n\n\n: F# -> F, G# -> G, D#m -> Dm, B -> A#, C# -> C\n: F#\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: F#, G#, D#m, B, C#\n\n\n: Optional\nJubaan hai fiki [F#] shaam se\n\nHui na tosey [F#] baat bhi\n\nBina mein tere [F#] bewazah\n\nHua hoon dekho [G#]aaj bhi [F#]\nKaroon mein ye [F#] guzarishein\n\nMohabbaton ka [F#] mol de\n\nNeendon mein meri [F#] khwab ka\n\nZara sa mitha [F#] bol de\nTu ban ja [F#] banja tu meri, tu ban ja\n\n[F#] banja, banja tu meri\n\n[G#]Tu ban ja ban[F#]ja banja tu [G#]meri\nIshqe de [F#]chasni [B] o [C#]mitthi\n\nmitthi [F#]chasni[B]\nMaina man[F#]gunga [A#7]dhup [D#m]dheemi dheemi\n\nMaina [G#]mangu chand[F#]ni\n\nMere [B]jeene mein tujh[D#m]se ho\n\nIshqe di chas[B]ni[G#] o mitthi mitthi [D#m]chas[B]ni[C#]\n: F#, B, F#, B, F#, B\n[F#]Mere khyalon mein jo [D#m]tu ho\n\nTo baatein hun mein [G#m]achchi\n\nachchi karta[B] haan..[C#]\n\nHmm [F#]dekhun subah subah jo [D#m]tujhe\n\nTo sara din [B]achcha hai guzarta\n\nYe [C#]kaisi teri [F#]arzoo,\n\n[D#m]Ye kaisi teri [B]khwahishein [F#]\n\nTujhise dekho main karoon\n\n[D#m]Teri hi far[B]mahishein [F#]\n[F#]Tu ban ja banja tu meri, [G#]tu ban ja\n\nban[F#]ja, banja banja tu [G#]meri\n\nIshqe de [F#]chasni[B] o mitthi\n\n[C#]mitthi [F#]chasni [B] [F#]\n: Ishqe Di Chashni\n\n\n: Bharat\n\n\n: Abhijit Srivastava\n\n\n: Irshad Kamil\n\n\n: Vishal & Shekhar\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: T-Series\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: May 2019\n: This melody has a very serenading tune. With the guitars and the esraj, Vishal and Shekhar have created an amazing fusion. The song has romance filled in every bit of it and the lyrics are extremely conversational. The soundtrack very subtly talks about how the beloved is enchantingly beautiful and heavenly. The lady love has been compared to a sweet, a delicacy which is intensely sugary and has a satisfying taste. The song is filled with metaphors and that is why this track is endearing to us. The tune is indeed very groovy and makes us sway to it. The beats are feet tapping and gentle. No heavy or exciting beats have been used which imparts to the song that slow and soulful feel. Abhijeet Srivastava has done a brilliant job. His performance is stellar and his smooth, tender and dulcet vocals are refreshing to hear. He has perfectly captured the feel of the song in his voice and that is the reason why we find this melody so lovely.\nIshqe di Chashni is a song meant to break all records. An extremely mellifluous soundtrack, this melody is very catchy and makes us hum the hook line – “Ishqe di Chashni” throughout the day. Like Dil Diyan Gallan and Lapata, this number is another path breaking song that has been filmed on Salman and Katrina, and their chemistry is indeed sizzling. Shot on breath taking locales, the video of this soundtrack is a feast to the eyes. This musical treat is totally bewitching and will always remain so in the future as well. Though in the movie’s context, the song portrays a love story setting from the 1942s, but in reality it caters to the love stories of all periods and generation. From the feature film soundtrack genre, this song is that sweet summer tempest after days of scorching heat. The number has a breath of newness in it and that’s why no matter how many times it has been played on loop, each time the song sounds as fresh as morning dew. The song has been made ideally for a romantic date with the lover, or as that song through which you want to say your feelings out loud to your beloved to make her yours.\'','\'New\'','Ishqe-Di-Chashni-Guitar-Chords---Strum---Bharat---Salman-Khan---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(273,'\'Guitar: Chale Aana Chords with Capo by Armaan Malik | Dede Pyar De - Abhijeet\'','\'Love is a bitter and sweet emotion. While there will be happiness and rays of sunshine somedays there will also be sadness and rainy days occasionally. This emotion has been melodiously captured in Chale Aana from De De Pyar De. Sung by the mellifluous Armaan Malik, it has been penned by Kunaal Vermaa and composed by Amaal Malik. The symphony has been created by a variety of exotic instruments like the flutes, the acoustic and the electric guitars, the live bass, the dholaks, the tablas, the violins and the violas and the strings. The guitar chords are very simple and can be picked up by the amateurs easily. The progression of the chords is subtle and harmonious. The rhythm is very groovy due to a signature 4/4 beat and a moderately paced tempo. The melody is a soothing rendition.\nThe original key scale is F#m while to serve the beginners with the easy chords we have used the guitar capo on the second fret so the chords of the song becomes Em, D, C, Am, & Bm.\n: D DU UDU or D DU DU D\n\n\n: D D UUU DUDU or D UUD D or DDU UDU\nd – Down Stroke on lower three strings\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: Accurate & Verified by Team\n: F#m\n: 2/4\n: 69\n\n\n: 2nd Fret\n: Em, D, C, Am, & Bm\n\n\n: F#m, C#m, D, Bm, & E\n:\n\n[Em] [C] [Em]\nJuda hum [Em]ho gaye ma[D]ana\n\nMagar ye [Bm]jaanlo ja[C]ana\n: [Em] [D] [C]\nJuda hum [Em]ho gaye ma[D]ana\n\nMagar ye [Bm]jaanlo ja[C]ana\nKbhi me [Am]yaad aau [D]toh\n\nChale aa[Bm]na… chale a[C]ana\n\nTumhe me [Em]bhul jaau[D]nga\n\nYe baatein [Bm]dil me na laa[C]na\nKbhi me [Am]yaad aau[D]to\n\nChale aa[Bm]na… chale a[C]ana\n:\n\n[Em] [D] [Bm] [C]\n\n[Am] [D] [Bm] [C]\nTha [C]kon mera, [A]ek tu he[G] tha[Em]\n\nSaa[C]nson se Jaada jo jaruri [D]tha\n\n[Em]Tere liye me kuch nhi leki[Bm]n\n\nMe[C]re liye tu mera sb kuch [D]tha\nNhi ja[Em]ana bhula Ka[D]rke\n\nYe baatein [Bm]tum he kehte [C]the\n\nRhi khushiy[Am]aan nhi [D]meri\n\nKe tum bhi [Bm]wakt jaise [C]the\nYhi tak [Em]tha safar ap[D]na\n\nTumhein hai [Bm]lot kar ja[C]ana\n\nKabhi me [Am]yaad aaun [D]to\n\nChale aa[Bm]na… chale aa[C]na\n:\n\n[Em] [D] [Bm] [C] [Am] [D]\n\n[Bm] [C]\n[C]Naa raa, naa [Em]na raa naa\n\nAye he he hey he he [Am]he\n\nHmm oh ho oh ho [Bm]ho\n\nChale aana… chale aa[Am]na[C]\n: Chale Aana\n\n\n: Armaan Malik\n\n\n: De De Pyaar De\n\n\n: Amaal Mallik\n\n\n Kunaal Vermaa\n\n\n: T-Series\n\n\n: P.M.K. Naveen Kumar\n\n\n Ankur Mukherjee & Roland Fernandes\n\n\n: Roland Fernanades\n\n\n: Satyajit Jamsandekar & Ratnadeep Jamsandekar\n\n\n: Satyajit Jamsandekar\n\n\n: May 2019\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n: We often have to part with our beloved due to various situations. Even if the parting is mutual, separations are always pathetic and agonising. This has been beautifully captured in the conversational and the touching lyrics of this track. Kunaal Vermaa has done a wonderful job in expressing those unsaid words into a melody so soulful. Amaal Malik is truly a maestro in all the senses. His creative genius is beyond praise, as with so many beautiful instruments he has created a piece of art that is not only mesmerising but also very refreshing. He has composed a beautiful contemporary fusion by mixing and matching the various instruments. And what adds further charm to this melody is the dulcet and euphonious voice of Armaan Malik. His gentle and smooth vocals are indeed spell binding. The passion that he brings out in his voice adds to that heart rendering feel of this serenading number.\'','\'New\'','Guitar--Chale-Aana-Chords-with-Capo-by-Armaan-Malik---Dede-Pyar-De---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(274,'\'Dhvani Bhanushali - Guitar: Vaaste Chords with Strumming - Abhijeet\'','\'| Released a day back and already trending at number 2 position on YouTube is the new single by Nikhil D’Souza and Dhvani Bhanushali named Vaaste. The song has been composed by the creative genius Tanishk Bagchi and the lyrics have been penned down by Arafat Mehmood. The melody is very happy and romantic with a catchy chorus. The soulful tune has actually made it even more popular and given the video 10 million views within a day.\n: D D UUD D\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: Accurate & Verified by Team\n: F\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: F, C, A#/Bb, Dm\n\n\n: D D UUD D\n:\n\n(F) (C) (Dm)(A#)(F)(C)\n\n(F) (C) (Dm)(A#)\nVaa(F)ste jaan bhi du\n\nMe (C)ganwa emaan bhi du\n\nKisma(Dm)to ka likha modd (A#)doon\n\nBadle (F)me main tere\n\nJo khu(C)da khudd bhi dey\n\nJana(Dm)tey sach kahu chhod (A#)du\n\nTum se jyaa(F)da me na jaanu\nTumse (C)khudko me pehchaanu\n\nTum ko(Dm)bs me apna maanu maa(A#)hiya\n\nVaas(F)te jaan bhi doon\n\nMe (C)ganwa emaan bhi du\n\nKisma(Dm)to kaa likha modd(A#)doon\n(F)Tere alaawa koi bhi khwaaish\n\n(C)Nai hai baaki dil mein\n\n(Dm)Kadam uthaaun… jahaan bhi jaun\n\n(A#)Tujh he se jaaun milne tere (F)liye mera safar\n\nTere (Dm)bina me jau ki(C)dhar\nTum se(F)zyaada me na jaanu\n\nTum se(C)khudko me pehchaanu\n\nTum ko(Dm)bas me apna maanu maahi(A#)yaa\n\nVaas(F)te jaan bhi doon\n\nMe(C)ganwa emaan bhi du\n\nKisma(Dm)to kaa likhaa modd (A#)du\nBadle (F)me mein tere\n\nJo khu(C)da khudd bhi dey\n\nJanna(Dm)tein sach kahu chhodd (A#)du\n\nTu he hai saw(F)era mera tu he ki(C)naara mera\n\nTu he hai (Dm)dariyaa mera\n\nKhudaa ka (A#)zariya mera\n\nTujhi se(F)hota shuru ye mera (C)karwaan\n\nTujhi pe(Dm)jo ki khatam\n\nYe mera (A#)sara jahaan\nVaas(F)te jaan bhi do\n\nMe (C)ganwa imaan bhi doon\n\nKisma(Dm)to ka likkha modd (A#)doon(C)\n: The song in the video begins with a very sweet and soft piano playing in the background and then the Antara is sung by Nikhil. However, in the audio version the song begins with the strumming of the guitar . The rhythm is moderately paced and feet tapping. Acoustic guitars have been predominantly used in the background along with the ukulele and the piano to add to the charm of this musical piece. The song is a smooth flow for about 3 minutes 16 seconds. It is very enthralling with a groovy beat that makes one sway to the song. The lyrics are romantic and charming. The duet talks about how the lovebirds can’t really do without each other and how they are deeply enamoured. Mehmood with ease has captured the beautiful emotions of love in the lyrics and presented it in this melody.\nThe singers have done a brilliant job. Nikhil, with his melodious and gentle voice weaves magic. But however the show stealer was Dhvani. After Sunidhi Chauhan and Shreya Ghoshal, Dhvani is the next big thing in the music industry of Bollywood. With hits like Leja re, Dilbar, Main teri hoon and Ishare tere, Dhvani with her euphonious and dulcet voice is all set to rule our hearts. Her voice is very sweet and smooth which is indeed captivating.\n: Vaaste\n\n\n: Dhvani Bhanushali & Nikhil D’Souza\n\n\n: Tanishk Bagchi\n\n\n Mehmood Arafat\n\n\n: Siddharth Gupta & Anuj Saini\n\n\n: T-Series\n\n\n: 2019\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n: Vaaste has already become a hit song because of the splendid performances of the singers and the sweet-toned music composition. The song has made the audience fall in love with it and keep on playing it on loop. The song is an appropriate date song and will make the lovers serenade to this soulful melody and do a little jig.\'','\'New\'','Dhvani-Bhanushali---Guitar--Vaaste-Chords-with-Strumming---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(275,'\'Guitar: Tu Thodi Der Chords with Capo & Strumming | Half Girlfriend - Abhijeet\'','\'| Music has the power to say those unsaid words, put feelings into words and then into a melody. The perfect example of this is Tu thodi der from Half Girlfriend. A recreated version of Farhan Saeed’s Tu Thodi dair, the song was picturised on Shraddha Kapoor and Arjun Kapoor. The melody was sung by India’s new nightingale Shreya Ghoshal and the enchanting Farhan Saaed. The song was released in 2017 and became one of the most played love songs of that year. The melody has an English reprised version titled Stay a little longer sung by Anushka Shahaney. The chords that we have used in the song are G, D, Em, C, & Am with the guitar capo on the second fret.\n: D UDUD DD DU & D UDUD UDUD DU (Refer to the embedded video)\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: A\n\n\n: 5\n: Required\n: 2nd Fret\n\n\n: G, D, Em, C, & Am\n\n\n: D UDUD DD DU & D UDUD UDUD DU\n[G]Dil charkhay ki [C]ikk tu dorri\n\n[G]Dil charkhay ki [C]ikk tu dorri\n\n[G]Sufi iska[C] rang haye\n[G]Isme jo tera[C] khaab piroyaa\n\n[G]Isme jo tera[C] khaab piroyaa\n\n[G]Neende bani[C] patang\nDil [G]bharta nhi\n\nAnkhein [C] rajti nhi\n\nDil [G]bharta nhi\n\nAnkhein [C] rajti nhi\nChaahe[D] kitna bhi dekhti [G] jau\n\nWakt[C] jaye me rokk na [D] pau\nTu thodi der[G]aur thehar ja[C] soniya\n\nTu thodi der[Em]aur thehar ja[D]\n\nTu thodi der[G]aur thehar ja[Am] zaalimaa\n\nTu thodi der[Em]aur thehar ja[D]\n: [G] [C] [G] [C]\n[G]Haye din tere bin ab[C] ji naa paye\n\n[G]Din tere bin ab [C]ji na paaye\n\n[G]Saas na leti [C]raat\n\n[G]Ishq kare [C] tere hothon sey\n\n[G]Ishq kare [C] mere hothon sey\n\n[G]Bs ikk teri [C]baat\nTeri[G] doori na sahu\n\nDurr[C] khud se rahu\n\nTeri[G] doori na sahu\n\nDurr[C] khud se rahu\nTere [C] pehloo me he reh [G] jaun\n\nTu he[C] samjhaan jo me [D] chaahu\nTu thodi der[G] aur thehar ja[C] sohneya\n\nTu thodi der[Em] aur thehar ja[D]\n\nTu thodi der[C] aur thehar ja[Am] zaalima\n\nTu thodi der[Em] aur thehar ja[G]\n:\n\n[G][C][Em][D]\n\n[G][C][Em][D]\nNaiyo[G] lagna… nahiyo lagna\n\nTere [C]bin dil mera\n\nNahiyo [Em] lagna… naiyo lagna\n\nTere [D]bin dil mera\n\nNaiyo[G] lagna… nahiyo lagna\n\nTere [C]bin dil mera\n\nNahiyo [Em] lagna… naiyo lagna\n\nTere [D] bin dil mera\nDil [G] minnatein kare\n\nNaa tu [C] jaa na pare\n\nDil [G] minnatein kare\n\nNa tu [C] ja naa pare\nTere [Em]jane sey ji na [G] paau\nTu thodi der [G] or thehar ja[C] sohneya\n\nTu thodi der [Em] or thehar ja[D]\n\nTu thodi der [C] or thehar ja[Am] zaalima\n\nTu thodi der [Em] or thehar ja[G]\n[Play the above paragraph one more time]\n: The song begins with a very soothing musical intro with the fusion of the sarangi and the guitar accompanied by a classical alaap by Shreya Ghoshal. The beats don’t begin there and the music itself starts to transport the hearer to another world- the world of love. Then as slowly the song progresses the beats start and it is a very slow and soft beat that is refreshing like the rain after the scorching heat. Through the 4 minutes and 56 seconds of the song, the composer Farhan Saaed himself, captivates us with a very heart rendering, soulful and melodious composition as he synchronizes the guitars with the sarangi, the piano and the harmonium. The song has a very sufi touch to it due to the sarangi and harmonium. What is applaud able here is the fusion of the instrument, and the beautiful music that is born of it.\nThe lyrics have been penned down by Kumaar and showcases the exact romantic feelings and emotions. The song is about the lover asking his beloved to stay a little longer and not depart early. An intensely emotional song, there is a beautiful smooth flow of the melody with some interludes that solely focus on the vocals and just one instrument like the piano in the background. This makes it a beautiful rendition so pleasing to hear. Shreya Ghoshal as usual mesmerizes us with her classically enriched and extremely sweet voice that makes the hearer drool over the song and keep on playing it on loop. Farhan Saaed also enchants us with his strong and deep voice.\n: Thodi Der\n\n\n: Half Girlfriend\n\n\n: Farhan Saeed & Shreya Ghoshal\n\n\n: Farhan Saeed\n\n\n: Kumaar\n\n\n Ali Mustafa\n\n\n: Ankur Mukherjee\n\n\n: Aditya Oke\n\n\n: Murad Ali Khan\n\n\n: 2017\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: Romantic Song\n: The song has won not only a lot of accolades and awards but also a lot of applause and hearts. A very soft contemporary fusion, this song resides within us. A perfect love song, this song will never get old and will continue to rule and entrance the coming generations.\'','\'New\'','Guitar--Tu-Thodi-Der-Chords-with-Capo---Strumming---Half-Girlfriend---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(276,'\'Music Teacher - Guitar: Phir Wahi Raat Hai Chords with Strumming - Abhijeet\'','\'| Today’s Bollywood hasn’t forgotten the Bollywood of the yesteryears. And the famous songs of the early era are being recreated and reprised beautifully to provide a tribute to those evergreen romantic melodies. Phir wahi raat hai from the film Music Teacher is a perfect example of this tribute. Recreated by Rochak Kohli, the melody has been voiced by the soothing Papon. The original song was sung by the unparalleled Kishore Kumar and penned by Gulzar.\n: DU(chuck) UU(chuck)\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\nC – Chuck/Mute Effect\n: B\n\n\n: 7\n\n\n: B, E, Em, F#m, D#m/Ebm, C#m/Dbm, G#m/Abm\n\n\n: DU(chuck) UU(chuck)\n\nPhir[E] wahi raat[B] hai\n\nPhir[F#m]wahi[E] raat hai khaab[B] ki\n\nPhir[E]wahi raat[B] hai\n\nPhir[F#m]wahi[E] raat hai khwaab[B] ki\n\nHo[B]raat bhar khwaab[C#m] me\n\n[G#m]Dekha karnge[E] tumhe\n\nFir[B] wahi raat[F#m] hai[E] [Em] [B]\n[B]Masoom si neend[E]mein\n\n[Em]Jb koi sapna[B] chaley\n\nHo[B] Hum ko bula lena[E]tum\n\n[Em]Palko ke pardey[B] taley\nHo[B] yeh raat hai khwaab[G#m] ki\n\n[D#m]Khwaab ki raat[E] hai\n\n[B]Phir whi raat[F#m]hai [E][Em][B]\nPhir[E]wahi raat[B] hai\n\nPhir[F#m] wahi[E] raat hai khwaab[B] ki\n[B]Kaanch ke khwaab[E] hai\n\n[Em]Ankhon me choobh[B] jaynge\n\nHo[B] palkon me lena[E] inhein\n\n[Em]Aankhon me rukk[B] jaaynge\nHoo[B] yeh raat hai khwaab[G#m] ki\n\n[D#m]Khwaab ki raat[E] hai\n\n[B]Fir wahi raat[F#m] hai [E][Em][B]\nPhir[E]wahi raat[B] hai\n\nPhir[F#m]whi[E] raat hai khwaab[B] ki\n\nFir[E]wahi raat[B]hai\n\nFir[F#m] wahi[E] raat hai khwaab[B] ki\nas\n\n[E]Raat hai khwaab[B] ki\n\n[E]Raat hai khwaab[B] ki\n: This classical romantic rendition relies solely on the guitars to give the background music and a very soft, mellow and serenading rhythm. Kohli has very creatively used the guitars to bring an unplugged and a classical feel. The chords are neither very difficult nor very easy. Since the melody relies only on the guitars the chords are very vital and the guitarist should have a bit of proficiency to pick the chords. However, mention must be made of the beauty of the chords as they alone impart that subtle serene and aesthetic feel to the song. The lyrics have been written by Gulzar and one cannot but expect deep meanings and metaphors hidden in them. This intensely romantic song expresses the love struck man’s feelings where he sees his beloved yet again on a night of dreams. The song is a gem. Originally sung by Kishore Kumar, it was quite a brave attempt on Papon’s part to sing this track since the perfection of Kishore Da’s voice in still unmatchable till date but Papon has done quite a commendable job here. His soothing and classically enriched vocals add a different charm to this recreated version. Papon has performed the song very emotionally and that is what makes us listen to this version again and again.\n: Phir Wohi Raat Hai\n\n\n: Papon\n\n\n Rochak Kohli\n\n\n: Music Teacher\n\n\n: Saregama\n\n\n: Mohit Dogra\n\n\n: 2019\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: Kishore Kumar\n\n\n: R.D.Burman\n\n\n Gulzar\n: With romance oozing out of the lyrics, this track is very blissful and soulful. The song transports us into a different world when listened to in solitude and brings the memories of the beloved lover flooding to the mind. Though the chords are slightly intricate, it is one of the best songs that can be covered on the guitar.\'','\'New\'','Music-Teacher---Guitar--Phir-Wahi-Raat-Hai-Chords-with-