back. She will forever be the best cook and the most beautiful woman in the world. Her lap will always be the safest place for you. To the woman whom we often take for granted but who persistently fights for us, stays with us and loves us unconditionally, who will give you the last piece of the cake even if she is hungry and look after you even when she is sick, to your lovely mother- Maa from the film RAW is a perfect tribute.\n: D#/Eb\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: G#, A#, D#, Cm\n(G#)Dhoonp jab(A#)sataaye\n\n(G#)Aanchal se(D#) dhakk leti ho\n\n(G#)Chot jb bhi(A#)aye\n\n(G#)Sang mere(D#) ro deti ho\n(Cm)Taveez jo(A#) me nikal(D#) du\n\n(G#)Pareshan ho(A#)jati ho(D#) tum\n\n(Cm)Kisi ki(A#)buri nazr lag(D#) jaaygi\n\n(G#)Pyaar se(A#)bataati ho(D#) tum\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati ho(D#)\n\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati ho(D#)\n\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati ho(D#)\n(D#)Khna (G#) tera jo naa(D#) maanu\n\nEkk(Cm) ajeeb saa(A#) dard(D#) hota hai\n\n(D#)Aankhein(A#)bhale he na(D#) roye\n\nPr(Cm) dil yeh(A#)mera(D#) rota hai\n(D#)Mujhe bhi(Cm) fikar teri hai(A#) maa\n\n(G#)Par me(A#)kehta (D#) nhi\n\n(D#)Tera yu(Cm) chupp rhna(A#)maa\n\n(G#)Acha mujhe(A#) lgta(D#) nhi\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati(D#) ho\n\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati(D#) ho\n\nOh(G#) maa(A#)aa yaad(G#) aati(D#) ho\n: This intensely emotional song was composed and sung by the brilliant Ankit Tiwari and penned by Prince Dubey. The song has used the sarod, some ethnic stringed instruments, the flute, the guitars and the piano very adeptly. The string instruments impart to the song that doleful effect. The guitars have simple chords that do not need a lot of proficiency on the part of the guitarist for learning and playing them. The guitar chords that have been played maintain a slow rhythm and give a soft beat to the song. The lyricist has done a very applaud able job here. The words are filled with emotions and beautifully showcase our feelings about our mothers. We often don’t appreciate their efforts or pay much attention to them but the lyrics very subtly point out to us how angelic our mothers are and how we cannot do without them. The song portrays the feelings of a boy who has to part for some months from his mother and the grief that he is in because of this parting. Ankit Tiwari has done a commendable job by singing the song in a mesmerising way and bringing out the emotions the lyrics wants to convey.\n: MAA\n\n\n: RAW\n\n\n: Ankit Tiwari\n\n\n Prince Dubey\n\n\n: Roopak Naigaonkar\n\n\n: Tapas\n\n\n: Times Music\n\n\n: Hindi (Non-Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: 2019\n: Maa is the perfect tribute to our wonderful mothers. The melody is relatable to everyone specially those who stay away from their mothers in a different city or place. One cannot help but shed a tear or two on hearing this song. So the next time you have a tiff with your mom or just want to appreciate her efforts play the chords on the guitar, if you are a guitarist; or just sing it to her and see how much it will make her smile and beam on you proudly.\'','\'New\'','Maa-Chords-by-Ankit-Tiwari---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(279,'\'KALANK - Guitar: Tabaah Ho Gaye Guitar Chords - Abhijeet\'','\'The best thing about a period film apart from the regal costumes and the majestic backdrops is the magnificent music. And when the composer is the creative genius Pritam Chakraborty himself, we can expect another masterpiece to be born. The song was penned by the poetic Amitabh Bhattachrya and sung by the melodious and mellifluous Shreya Ghoshal. The song sings about the pangs of separation undergone by the heartbroken lover and the phenomenal Madhuri Dixit’s enchanting Kathak performance keeps the viewers under a spell.\n: D UUD UUD\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: Em\n\n\n: 7\n\n\n: Em, D, G, Cm, Am, C, B\n(Em)Di nahi (D)dua bhale\n\nNa(G)di kbhi badd(Em)dua\n\nNa khaffa (D)hue na hum\n\nHue kbhi be(Em)waffa\n(D)Tum magar(Cm)a bewaffa ho (G)gye\n\nKyu khaffa ho (Am)gye\n\nKe tum se juda hokey(D)hum\nTabaah ho(Em)gaye\n\n(D)Tabaah ho (C)gye… (D)tabha\n\nho (Am)gaye (D)tabaah ho (C)gaye(Em)\nfir akkhiyaan me preet ki teri\n\nReet jaga(Am)jana\n\nMohe(B)chodd ke jane ki khaatirr\n\nHe(C)laut ke a jaana\nFir akhiyaan me preet ki teri\n\nReet jaga(Am)jana\n\nMohe(B)chhod ke jane ki khaatir\n\nHe(C)laut ke aa jana\nHa (D)ghair ke (Cm)humnawa ho (G)gye\n\nKyu khaffa ho (Am)gye\n\nKi tum se juda hokey(D)hum\n\nTabaah ho (Em)gaye(D)\nTabaah ho(C)gye (D)tabaah\n\nho(Am)gye\n\n(D)Tabaah ho(C)gaye(Em)\nHa sajdey me hum ne(D)maanga tha\n\n(Am)Umar humaari bhi lg (G)jaye (D)tum ko\n\n(Em)Khudse he tauba (D)krte the\n\n(Am)Nazar na humaari lag(G)jaye (D)tum ko\nHa (Em)sajdey me humne (D)manga tha\n\n(Am)Umar humaari bhi lag (G)jaye (D)tumko\n\n(Em)Khudse hi tauba(D)krte the\n\n(Am)Nazar na humaari lag(G)jaaye (D)tum ko\n(Em)Hum (D)magar (C)…(Em)\n\nHum(D)magar na(G)gawaara tumhe kis tarah ho(Am)gye\n\nKi tumse juda hokey(D)hum\nTabaah ho(Em)gaye\n\n(D)Tabaah ho… (C)gaye… (D)tabaah\n\nho (Am)gaye… (D)tabaha ho (C)gaye(Em)\n: This song has used diverse exotic instruments very creatively and artfully. The instruments used are- bagpipes, ney, qanun, Sitar, glockenspiel, bass, tabla, dholak, strings, violins, viola, cello, contrabass. The orchestra that has been performed here is indeed a masterful piece of work and it is by far the most unique song ever composed by Bollywood. The track very creatively synchronises the various instruments and the percussions to give that immensely heavy and classical beat making the melody ideal for a performance on Kathak or Bharatnatyam. The song has the Padhant recitals very marvellously performed. This melody is rich in classical overtones and Shreya Ghoshal has done a very commendable job as usual. Her intensely rich classical and dulcet vocals have given this melody that mellow feel and a doleful aura. The lyrics are wistful and pensive and grieve about the bittersweet parting from the beloved that is causing a lot of agony to the heartbroken lover. The song captures the feel and mood of an ethnic ancient period, essentially the 1940s backdrop. The music itself wins our hearts. The alaap, antara and the mukhra have a very soulful effect and the chorus is quite splendid as the singers have done a praiseworthy job there. The song can be covered on other western instruments like the piano and the guitar, but the guitar chords are a bit challenging in this case and a bit of proficiency is required on the guitarist’s part.\n: Tabaah Ho Gaye\n\n\n: Kalank\n\n\n: Shreya Ghoshal\n\n\n: Pritam\n\n\n Amitabh Bhattacharya\n\n\n: Zee Music Company\n\n\n: Meira Segal\n\n\n: Tamer Pinarbasi\n\n\n: Umashankar Shukla, Aparna Doedhar & Zuber Sheikh\n\n\n: DJ Phukan & Aditya Dev\n\n\n: Raj Kumar Dewan\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: 2019\n: Due credit has to be given to the entire musical team who have worked hard to make Tabaah ho gaye an evergreen historic song with rich musical overtones and a sullen and sombre mood simultaneously with perfect beats for a dance performance. The song is one of a kind, as it can be enjoyed by the dejected lover in quietude and also can be enjoyed by dancers who can perform this to earn appreciation and accolades.\'','\'New\'','KALANK---Guitar--Tabaah-Ho-Gaye-Guitar-Chords---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(280,'\'Yasser Desari - Guitar: Meri Hasi Chords with Strumming - Abhijeet\'','\'We suggest you to play the chords of meri hasi song with D DUDU over these 6 chords Fm, D#, C, G#, C#, A#m\n: D DUDU\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: Fm\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: Fm, D#, C, G#, C#, A#m\n\n\n: D DUDU\n(Fm)Meri hasi mein chupey dard\n\n(D#)Pehchaanta hai tu han han\n\n(Fm)Haan aa(D#) haaa…aa haa(C) aaa(Fm)\n(Fm)Meri hasi me chhupey dard\n\n(D#)Pehchaanta hai tu\n\n(Fm)Har dua me mujhe he mujhe\n\n(D#)Mangta hai tu\n\n(G#)Baarisho me(A#m) mere ashq\n\nPehchaan(D#)ta hai tu\nKyun ki(G#) mujh se jaada(D#