ven if you touch your lover’s fingers you are forbidden to hold hands. The song very beautifully creates the situations only to forbid them and in this forbiddance is hidden the wish to commit those actions as the taste of the forbidden fruit is always sweeter. Lagnajita Chakraborty with her mesmerizing voice weaves magic and bewitches us. Just like Basanta eshe geche, Preme pora baron has won all our hearts by making us play it on loop and serenade to it.\n: Pora Mon\n\n\n: Ke Tumi Nandini\n\n\n: Raj Barman & Trisha Chatterjee\n\n\n Prasen\n\n\n: Amlaan\n\n\n: Raja Chowdhury\n\n\n: Raja Chowdhury\n\n\n: SVF Music\n: Soumyajyoti Ghosh\n\n\n: Bengali (Bangla)\n\n\n: 2019\n\n\n: India\n: The song is a very unique composition with dulcet vocals and a euphonious music and it is the ideal song to be strummed on the guitar beside a bonfire or in a jamming session with your friends.\'','\'New\'','Pora-Mon-Chords-with-Strumming--Easy----Ke-Tumi-Nandini---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(282,'\'Title Track - Guitar: Shudhu Tomari Jonno Chords - Abhijeet\'','\'Want to express your emotions and love to your beloved in Bengali on the Bengali Valentine’s day a.k.a Saraswati Puja? Well the perfect song is right there for you- Sudhu Tomari Jonne from the Bengali film Sudhu Tomari Jonne. Sung by the most loved duo of the Tollywood music industry- Arijit Singh and Shreya Ghoshal, this intensely romantic melody was composed by Indraadip Dasgupta and penned by Prasen. The slow and soulful melody ignites us with a different sort of love and romance.\n: D D DUDU or D D UUD DDU\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: D\n\n\n: 7\n\n\n: D, C, A, Bm, F#m, E, & Em\n\n\n: D D DUDU or D D UUD DDU\n(D)Hote pari roddurr, hote pari\n\nbrishti… hote pari(Bm)rasta tomaari jo(Am)nay\n\nHote pari (D)bodnam… hote pari\n\ndaknaam, hote pari (Bm)soti, tomaari\n\njo(A)nne\n\nHote pari(D)gol po tumi kachhe\n\n(Bm)tanle, hote pari (F#m)jaanla eyi ha(Em)wwa o tomar\n\nkaro(A)ne\nShudhu tumi(D)chau jodi\n\nSajaabo(E)abar nodi\n\nShudhu tumi(D)chau jodi\n\nSajaabo(E)abar nodi\n\nEshechi hazaar baaro(A)ne\nShu(D)dhu to(C)mari jo(G)nne Suuh(D)dhu to(C)maari\n\njo(D)nne(A)\n\nShu(D)dhu to(C)mari jo(G)nne Suuh(D)dhu to(C)maari\n\njo(D)nne\nKotha dilo roddurr, kohta dilo\n\nbrishti, kotha dilo(Bm)rasta tomari jo(A)nney\n\nKheladhulo song(D)shaar ashaa jaaowa baar-baar\n\nRaaji holo (Bm)icche tomari jon(A)ne\n\nHote pari(D)golpo tumi kache(Bm)tanle\n\nHote pari(F#m)jaanla ei hao(Em)wa o tomar\n\nkar(A)on\nSudhu tumi(D)chaau jodi\n\nSajaabo(E)abar nodi\n\nShudhu tumi (D)chaau jodi\n\nSajaabo a(E)bar nodi\n\nEshechi hazaar baro(A)ne\nShuuu(D)dhu to(C)mari jo(G)nne Shuu(D)dhu\n\nto(C)mari jo(D)nne(A)\n\nShuuu(D)dhu to(C)mari jo(G)nne Shuu(D)dhu\n\nto(C)mari jo(D)nne\n: The track begins with a beautiful music played on the guitar and the sitar. The instruments that have been used are- guitars, violins, the sitar and the sarod. The music is a beautiful fusion of the western and the India instruments. The guitar chords are simple and easy for the amateurs to learn them in a jiffy. The chords give a very slow and euphonious beat. The song gains half of its charm and emotions from the symphony created by these musical instruments. The lyrics are intensely powerful. Prasen has won our hearts by very poetically capturing the emotions we face when we are blind in love. The song talks about how the lovers can be something different, something powerful and something else only for the beloved. The song is charming by all means and the lyrics are very emotionally relatable. Mention has to be made of the magical duo that has enchanted us by this duet. Arijit Singh mesmerizes us once again by his rich and deep voice, while Shreya Ghoshal performs the song with all her heart making it a bewitching number. The singers have carved the emotions by their classically enriched voices and Ghoshal with her enthralling and charmingly sweet voice hypnotises us to listen to this song repeatedly.\n: Sudhu Tomari Jonno\n\n\n: Arijit Singh & Shreya Ghoshal\n\n\n: Arindam Chatterjee\n\n\n Prasen\n\n\n: Shree Venkatesh Films (SVF)\n\n\n: Ankur Mukherjee\n\n\n: Rohan Roy\n\n\n: Prateek Srivastava\n\n\n: Rahul Chatterjee\n\n\n: Bengali (Bangla)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n: 2015\n: The song is filled with a feeling of unconditional love. This blissful rendition is very slow and serene. So if you want to propose any Bengali beauty, well play this song on the guitar for her and see how she goes gaga over you.\'','\'New\'','Title-Track---Guitar--Shudhu-Tomari-Jonno-Chords---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(283,'\'Aur Kuch Baki Chords by Yasser Desai - Abhijeet\'','\'So while you were travelling in the bus, you saw a beautiful lady who enchanted you and you instantly fell in love at first sight. You don’t know whether you’ll ever meet her again or not but have this amazing feeling and instant connection. We often fall in love at first sight with different hopes but sometimes we feel helpless at our inability to express the feelings. Well Yasser Desai’s single – Aur Kuch Baki Hai exactly is the song that you will relate too. The song was composed by the talented Harshit Saxena and was penned by Dev Narayan.\n: D D DUD\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: F\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: F, Gm, Bb/A#, Dm, C, & Am\n\n\n: D D DUD\n(F)Lahfzon Se Kuch Na Bataana\n\nAnkhiyo Me Muskuraana\nLaf(C)zo Se Kuch Na Bat(F)aana\n\nAnkhiyo Me Muskuraana\nHo(A#) Gya Rey Tujhse (F)Pyaar\n\nDil(A#) Gya Me Tujh pe(F)Haar\n\nHo(A#) Gya Rey Tujhse (F)Pyaar\n\nDil(A#) Gya Me Tujh pe(F)Haar\nOh(Dm)Piya Oh.. (Am)Piyaa aa(Gm)aa\n\nAur Kuch (C) Baki Ho To(F)Bolo\n\nOh(A#)Piya aa(Gm)\n\nAur Kuch (C)Baaki Ho To(F)Bolo\n\nOo(A#)Piya aa(Gm)\n\nAur Kuch (C)Baaki Ho To(F)Bolo\n(F)Naino Ke Kinaare-Kinaare\n\n(Dm)Chaahato Ke Dhaare-Dhaare\n\n(F)Aakr Basa Rey Meri (A#)Dhadkano\n\nMe(C)Tu\n(F)Nindiyaan Ki Chori Bhi Ki\n\n(Dm)Or Seena Jori Bhi Ki\n\n(Am)Shaamil