 could make one forget everything for a few moments and I will agree it is worth it. The video features Akshay Kumar trying to woo Parineeti Chopra, while sporting his mane. The lyrics have been penned down by Tanishk Bagchi, who has also composed it. In the movie, Akshay Kumar is a military commander of 21 Sikh soldiers who are fighting against many Afghani invaders.\nThe song starts with Parineeti stopping a horse drawn carriage that Akshay boarded and when he turns around to see her running after the carriage his eyes stay glued to her. After a couple of incidents throughout the movie they fall in love and tie the knot in a gurudwara. The instrumental and tone of the song is catching and follows a continuous beat, making its presence felt while being highly prominent. The lyrics have been thought of well and beautifully put together. The type of music is perfect for an emotionally romantic song. This song is perhaps the only part of the movie where there is extra focus on the love story and does not take the spotlight off the battle, which is the sign of a well planned movie. The song is able to deliver a strong enough message in a few minutes which carries on with the audience for the remaining part of the movie.\n: D D UUD D or DD UUD DUDUD\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: Bb/A#\n\n\n: 5\n\n\n: Bb/A#, F, Gm, D#/Eb, & Dm\n\n\n: D D UUD D or DD UUD DUDUD\n(A#)Tujh ko yaad hai bata\n\nBhooli bisri wo jagah\n\nUsme (D#)lipti wo subha\nUs ek(A#)aangan ko bna\n\nTu (Dm)zameen or aas(A#)maa\n\nFirta (Gm)kyu hai yu tanhaa(A#)\n(Gm)Doorie(F)jo darmiyaa hai\n\n(D#)Tujhme or aashiyaa hai\n\n(Gm)Karde (F)kam faasley tu ooh.. (A#)oh oh…(D#)\n(Gm)Dastak tu dey(F)yahaan pe\n\n(D#)Sunte hai der wahaan pe\n\n(Gm)Krde kam(F)faasale zara(A#) (D#)\n\n(Gm)Ooh.. (D#)oo oh…\nTu (A#)chodh (F)zidd ko\n\n(Gm)Oo.. (D#)ooh…\n\n(A#)Fakeera(F) ghar a(D#)aja\nFakira ghar aaja…\n\nFakeera ghar aja…\n\nOo oh…\nAj(D#)nabi seharo (A#)ki tu\n\nKyu bahon me(F)soye\n\nYu gintaa(Cm)sitaarey\n\nMaj