re (C)humsafar\n\nKya tujhe(G)itni si bhi (C)khabar\n: [G]\n(G)Sun mere (C)humsafar\n\nKya tujhe(G)itni si bhi (C)khabar\n\nKi teri (G)saasein chalti(C) jidhr\n\nRahunga (D)bs wahi umr (G)bhr\n\nRahunga (D)bs wahi umr (G)bhr… haye\n(Em)Jitni haseen yeh(Bm)mulaakate hai\n\n(C)Unse bhi pyaari teri (G)batein hai\n\n(Em)Baato me teri jo kho (Bm)jate hai\n\nAau na (Am)hosh mein me (D)kabhi\n\nBaanho mei(Am)hai teri (G)zindagi… (D)haye\n(G)Sun mere(C)humsafar\n\nKyaa tujhe(G) itni si bhi(C)khabar\n: [G] [C] [G] [C]\n(G)Zaalima tere ishqch(C) me\n\n(G)Ho gyi yaa (C)kamli…(G)haye(C)…\n(G)Main to yoon khada\n\n(G)Kis soch me pada tha\n\n(C)Kese ji rha tha me(D)diwaana\n(G)Chupke se akey tune\n\n(C)Dil me samaake tune\n\n(Bm)Chedh diya (C)kaisa yeh(D)fassana\noh… (Em)muskuraana bhi tujh he se (Bm)seekhaa hai\n\n(C)Dil lagaane ka tu he(G)tareeka hai\n\n(Em)Aitbaar bhi tujh he se (Bm)hota hai\n\nAau naa(Am)hosh mein me(D)kabhi\n\nBaanhon me(Am)hai teri (G)zindagi… (D)haaye…\n(G)Hai nhi tha (C)pta\n\nKe tujhe(G) maan loonga (C)Khudaa\n\nKi teri (G)galliyon me is(C) kadar\n\n(D)Aaunga ab harr(G)pehar\n(G)Sun mere(C)humsafar\n\nKya tujhe (G)itni si bhi(C)khabar\n\nKi teri (G)saasein chalti(C)jidhar\n\nRahunga (D) bas wahi umar (G)bhar\n\nRahunga (Bm)bs wahi umarr (C)bhar… (G)haaye\n(G)Zaalima tere ishq chh main…\n: Aye Mere Humsafar\n: Akhil Sachdev\n\n\n: Badrinath Ki Dulhania\n\n\n: 2017\n\n\n Akhil Sachdev\n\n\n: Akhil Sachdev\n\n\n: Hindi (Bollywood)\n\n\n: India\n\n\n Veljon\n\n\n: T-series\nHumsafar begins with just Mansheel’s voice. Her part of the song gave a Qawali touch that was indeed very emotional and soothing. Sachdeva did his debut here but it was quite a path breaking performance . His voice is quite similar to Atif Aslam’s voice and the song therefore has been sung in a low scale. Like Atif, Sachdeva has the same depth and a bit of baritone. So the song has a different groove and an amorous aura about it. The lyrics are very passionate and talks about how important the beloved is to the lover, and how she has kept him captivated and enchanted. Any girl will melt into ice if her lover dedicates and sings this to her. The song has a happy note to it. The 8/8 beats are slow and soothing. What makes the song more enthralling is the transition of beats from slow to fast and then again to slow. The guitar, the synthesizer and the use of a mouth instrument was indeed a brilliant idea as that made the song sound even more romantic.\nThe song is very catchy. It won’t be a difficult task to cover it on other instruments like piano or guitar. The vocals are powerful and reach out to the listeners with just the sole quality of emotions hidden in them. The song has a beautiful meaning and through the romantic lyrics, it speaks a lot to the listeners. The mixture of Punjabi and Hindi and usage of some Urdu words imparts to the song a different sensation. The song has a span of about 3 minutes and 35 seconds and in this duration it doesn’t fail to win the hearts of those listening to it for the first time. This serenading melody is blissful and will make you listen to it on loop. It promises one thing that it will serve as a mood enhancer on a date night or act as a good apology after a fight. Sachdeva has done a brilliant job indeed and has given us a melody that is praiseworthy.\'','\'New\'','GUITAR--Sun-Mere-Humsafar-Chords-with-Strumming---Badrinath-Ki-Dulhania---Abhijeet','C Major,D Minor','new','new','new','C Major','new','D uud udu'),(301,'\'Half Girlfriend - Guitar: Main Phir Bhi Tumko Chahunga Chords [w/wo Capo] - Abhijeet\'','\'| Heartbroken? Going through a break up? Faced a rejection from your crush? Well, if you are suffering from any of the three situations and need to let that heart wrenching grief out, Main phir bhi tumko chahunga from Half Girlfriend will act as a tonic to your grief-stricken souls. The melody was released in 2017 and was filmed on the beautiful Shraddha Kapoor and handsome Arjun Kapoor. The song was composed by Mithoon and the soulful lyrics were penned by Manoj Muntashir. Written in the Nazm style, the song won the Listener’s Choice of the Year, from the 10th Mirchi Music Awards in 2018. The song also has a reprise version and another one sung by the female lead actress.\nThe song starts with a sad tune played on the piano that instantly harmonies with the sorrowful, grave mood of the heartbroken lover. The king of sad songs, Arijit Singh yet again wins our heart by pouring all his emotions into the song. His velvety and somber voice really touches the strings of our hearts. But what is more appealing is the soft and the melodious voice of Shasha Tirupati, which is really soothing and graceful to hear. The serenading voice of Shasha and the resounding voice of Arijit gives the listeners just that exact feeling experienced on parting or getting rejected by the beloved. The duration of the song is of about 5 minutes 52 seconds. The song is a soulful rendition indeed. However it’s not just the singers but also the contribution of the musical instruments used that lends the song it’s intended feel. Here a variety of instruments have been synchronized together. Beginning with the piano and a slow guitar strumming at the background with Arijit’s intense voice and slowly then putting on the beats was a wonderful idea that actually made the song so endearing. Another noteworthy fact was the Jugalbandi of Indian and Western instruments like the flute and the piano, which was played between the paragraphs- that did the magic and won the hearts of the people.\nThe lyrics are the next most important factor that gave the song it’s actual power. Muntashir brought out the exact feelings one faces when he or she loves with all the might but can’t be with the loved one. It expresses how the smitten lover will still love, wait and continue his search for the beloved throughout his life. Even if they aren’t together, the lover will remain loyal and love and wait for the beloved forever. This is what the every heartbroken person can relate too and therefore the song won its accolades and more than a hundred million views and was claimed as one of the most played songs of Bollywood.\nMain phir bhi tumko chahunga has a different emotional connection with the people and the mellow, sad song can remind you of a parted lover from the past. Though the song talks of unconditional love, it is romantic by all means, and can transport you into a world of happy memories of past and all sorts of emotions when listened to in quietude. The song will be a forever favorite to all the music lovers and can be rightfully called the ‘Lover’s song of the decade’.\n: 97\n\n\n: A#m/Bb minor\n\n\n: 4/4\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: A#m, Fm, C#, G#, D#m, F#\n: We have also shared the easy/capo version in this article\n\nTum [A#m]mere ho [Fm]is pal[C#]mere ho\n\nKal [G#]saayad [A#m]ye [F#]alam na rhe\n\nKuch [A#m]aisa ho tum[C#]tum na[Fm]rho\n\nKuch [C#]aisa [G#]ho hum… [F#]hum naa rahey\nYe[C#]raastey alag ho jae\n\n[F]Chaltey-chaltey hum [A#m]kho jaein\nMain[A#m]phir bhi tumko [G#]chahunga\n\nMain[C#]fir bhi tumko [F#]chaahunga\n\nMain[A#m]phir bhi tumko [G#]chahunga\n\nMain[C#]fir bhi tumko [F#]chaahunga\nIs[A#m]chaahat me mar[G#]jaunga\n\nMe[C#]phir bhi tum ko[F#]chahunga\nMeri [D#m]jaan me har[G#]khaamosi le\n\nTere[F]pyr ke nagmein[A#m]gaungaa[F#]..mmm[G#]mm\nMain[A#m]phir bhi tum ko[G#]chahunga\n\nMain [C#]phir bhi tum ko[F#]chahunga\n\nIs[A#m]chaaht me mae[G#]jaungaa\n\nMain[C#]phir bhi tumko [F#]chahunga\n[F#]Aise zaruri ho[A#m]mujh ko tum\n\n[F#]Jese [G#]hawaaein [A#m]saaso ko\n[F#]Aise talaashoon [A#m]me tum ko\n\n[F#]Jesse ki[G#]per [A#m]zameeno ko\n[G#]Hasna yaa[A#m]rona ho mjhe\n\n[G#]Pagal sa[A#m]dhundu me tumhe\n\nKal [F#]mujhse mohabatt [A#m]ho na ho\n\nKal [F#]mujh ko ijaajat [A#m]ho na ho\n[D#m]Tootey dil ke [G#]tukdey lekar\n\nTere [F]darr pe he rh [A#m]jaunga..[F#]…mmm[G#]mmm\nMain[A#m]phir bhi tum ko[G#]chahunga\n\nMain [C#]phir bhi tumko[F#]chahunga\n\nIs[A#m]ch