ough?\nTalking of love and lovers, this song is sure to remind you of the times when you wanted someone really badly and were chasing their attention. It isn’t sad but, it does have a feeling of longing attached to it. While you want them and the very thought of having them makes you happy, you don’t really have them yet. Such paradox is life.\nWhile you can dance to the beats, it could also be a song you listen to on a night you miss your lover. Such dynamic nature is not very common in the songs we hear today. Such perks justify the 200 million views that the song has on YouTube. I am sure I am not the only one who loves it!\nLe ja le ja is a breath of fresh air. The music is refreshing and mesmerizing. Dhvani’s voice is just as blissful as her very vibe. The lyrics are apt and have such meaning attached to them, while being fun at the same time. The piece is one of its kind and brings back the old school traditional idea of love.\n: A#m/Bbm\n\n\n: 4\n\n\n: Bbm/A#m, Db/C#, Ab/G#, F#\nYou(A#m) waant(C#) me\n\nYou got’ta(G#) know(C#) me\n\nIf you(A#m) love(C#)me\n\nYou gotta(G#) show(C#)me\n(C#)Leja laja\n\n(C#)leja leja…\n\nleja(G#) leja(C#)re\nMjhse(G#) durr khi na(C#)ja\n\nBs(G#) yhi-kahi rh(F#)ja\n\nMe(G#) teri diwaani(A#m) rey\n\n(G#)Ahfsos tujhe hai(C#) kya [Two Times]\nTeri(C#) meri kahaani(A#m) nai ban gyi\n\nTu(C#) mera ho gya me(G#) teri hoo(C#) gyi\n\nJaha(C#) jaye tu(F#) sung mujhe(G#) lejaa\n\n(C#)leja leja… leja leja…\nLeja(C#) leja re Mehaki(F#) raat mein\n\n(G#)Churaake saare(C#) rang leja\n\nSaare(G#) rang le(C#)ja\nRati(C#)rati me bhigun(F#) saathme\n\n(G#)Tu aisi mulaa(C#)kaat deja\n\nMula(G#)kaat de(C#)ja\n(C#)Back it up now…\n\nGet them up..\nYe(C#)h teri meri baate\n\nYe(G#)h meethe-meethe(A#) pal\n\nYe(C#)h bhige-bhige mosam\n\nMile(G#) na hume(A#) kal [Two Times]\n(A#m)Tere liye me hu\n\n(F#)Mere liye tu hai\n\n(G#)Dar kis bat ka(C#) hai\n(C#)I wanna know you right…\n\n(F#)Boy you got me roadside\n\n(G#)Now! I wanna hear you(C#)say\n\nJahan(C