 Irshad Kamil are brilliantly penned down. The words are crafted into a poetry of love and companionship .The music directors, Atul and Ajay practiced blend orchestration with electronic synthesizers and rock in some parts which made the song interesting. There is an amazing flute solo in the song which was appreciated among the youth. Other than the flute solo, there was also a lot of use of the violin which was pleasing to the ears. The vocals are also good and well controlled.\nThe song can be played with the 6 chords and song has it’s scale in Dbm/C#m and the chords that we have used in the progression are A, B, Dbm/C#m, E, Gbm/F#m & Gb/F#\n: Dbm/C#m\n: 86\n\n\n: 4/4\n\n\n: 6\n\n\n: A, B, Dbm/C#m, E, Gbm/F#m, Gb/F#\n: [C#m] [A] [B] [C#m] [Two Times]\n[C#m]Ann bann teri meri thi\n\n[C#m]Teri meri hain\n\n[C#m]Bat ye jhuthi[B] hai[E][F#m]\n[C#m]Pal bhar oron ki tarah\n\n[C#m]Mana tu zara\n\nPyaar mee ruthi [B]hai[E][F#m]\n[C#m]Apni [B]abb ho na [E]baat khi\n\n[C#m]Aise [B]halaat [E]nhi\n\n[C#m]Mana [B]badli hai [E]teri nazar\n\n[F#m]Badle [B]jazzbat nhi\nChhodey se chutegi tu [C#m]na [A][B]\n\n[B]Chhodey se chhootgi tu [C#m]naa[A] [B]\n\n[B]Itna ho jaaunga [G#m]tera[A] [B]\n\nAage se ruthegi tu[C#m]na\n: [C#m]\n[C#m]Ann bann teri meri thi\n\n[C#m]Teri meri he\n\n[C#m]Baat ye jhuthi [B]hai[E][F#m]\n\n[C#m]Pal bhar oro ki tarah\n\n[C#m]Maana tu zara\n\n[C#m]Pyaar me rutthi [B]hai[E][F#m]\n[C#m]Kam zara zara haske roz [A]tadpan\n\n[A]Kia karu pr hai ye bhi [B]uljhan\n\n[B]Lge mujhe hasna jhuth [E]mera[G#]\n[C#m]Dr lga rhe mujhko roz ye[A]bhi\n\n[A]Tere haathon bhul se[B] bhi\n\n[B]Jaaye khi dil na tutt [E]mera\nKhair[F#]ab jo mile [B]mujhe\n\nWo sb [G#m]mohabbat hai[E] teri\n\nKhair [F#]had se guzarna [G#m]bhi to\n\nEk aadat hai [E]meri\n[C#m]Tanha [B]rhna [E]aasan kaha\n\n[F#m]Mushkil ye[B]kaam [E]lage\n\n[C#m]Itna sach[B]hai tu[E]maan isse\n\nHum [F#m]tere [B]nam lge\nChhode se chhutegi tu[C#m]naa[A][B]\n\n[B]Chhodey se chhuutegi tu [C#m]naa[A][B]\n\n[B]Itna ho jaa