dagi, coupled with the prominent lyricist Amitabh Bhattacharya, this song is definitely one that’s going to stay on top of the charts for some time.\nDev Negi who we know for his hits like Badri Ki Dulhania has just proved why he deserves to be one of the elite singers of Bollywood. His gentle yet romantic voice is surely going to sweep listeners off their feet. The song ends with you wanting to hear more of it and the short length of 2 minutes and 22 seconds just doesn’t seem to be enough for this addictive and peppy song. This song shows the perfect on-screen chemistry of Sushaant Singh Rajput with the newcomer Sara Ali Khan. The song is a romantic song with all the verses showering love and affection towards the girl. The opening verse of the song gets the lyrics stuck in your head and it’s exactly that kind of song that you’re going to be playing on repeat for quite some time. This song goes perfectly in sync with the story of the movie which focuses with a young Hindu girl falling in love with a Muslim guy in the midst of the Uttarakhand floods.\nThe lyrics of the song- “Do nain sitaare hai chand sa mukhda” have been used to portray the beauty of the actress. These words mean that the eyes are sparkling like stars and the face has been compared to the moon to signify the beauty. Some parts of the song have been written in Urdu, which makes the lyrics sound even better than they do. The beauty of the lyrics is that it’s easy to understand, it’s like a regular conversation has been converted into lyrics and has been given a catchy melody.\nThe chorus is extremely melodious, something people haven’t heard before. The brilliant music by Amit Trivedi ensures that the song is really good to listen to. The dhol, the shehnai, gives the music such a beautiful, ethnic touch. The backing vocals, the strings, everything is very well played out together to give this song a stronger punch of vibrancy and freshness. Least to say, this song is definitely going to turn out to b