nal song and the lyrics really leave a lasting effect on the listeners. Atif Aslam is known to sing the most beautiful melodies and really elevates the song on another level making the track tread the path of immediate success; and this talent of his has struck a chord with today’s youth on such a level that it almost became the fastest song to reach at 20 million plus views in 24 hours.\nThe listeners don’t listen to this track from their ears but their hearts, the lyrics are magical. When I first listened to Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan’s version, I fell in love and was almost sure that no rendition or recreation could surpass this. But I was struck clean bowled when I gave this 3 minute song a listen. One whole listen was all it took me to put it and claim it as a world wind change in Bollywood Love Songs. Beware, this song might just hold a special place in your heart; the use of acoustic guitar, the melody, the beats they all bind together so well, but again there is a touch of the shehnai and harmonium which gives the song an earthy tone.\nWe as listeners sometimes forget the strength in the singer’s voice and the importance of it, Atif Aslam’s voice is the most refined, it’s extremely smooth and it feels as if he’s hitting the hit notes with no efforts. Plus, the tonal quality is par excellence; it’s majestic and really pulls the strings in your heart.\nThis song, in terms of emotionalism reminds me of “Main Rang Sharbato Ka” which again was such a heart touching track, and the whole song is driven by its lyric, just like this one. If this song is a hit it’s almost solely because of the lyrics and the melody. Besides that, it’s a very easy song to learn on your guitar and perhaps maybe with a little bit of practice and training an easy song to sing too.\n\nThis song really, in its true spirits, does justice to the original song, the impact of the lyrics never fades and remains intact, it really compels you to feel each and every word of the song on the deepest level.\nIt might even be safe to say that this song is one of the greatest tributes to a legend.\nThe original scale of Dekhte Dekhte song is in Am. The chords that we’ve used in this song are Am, G, F (without capo). If you would like to play it using the capo then place your capo on the 5th fret and use Em, D, & C Chord to play your capo version of this melodious song. Below we’ve shared the chord progression in detail along with the strumming pattern.\n: D (c) UU (c) U or D UUD UUD\n\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n\n(c) – Chuck Sound\n\n\n: 5th Fret\n\n\n: Em, D, C\n\nIf you would like to play it with your Capo, then you need to place your guitar capo on the 5th Fret of your instrument then the chords of the song will become Em, D, C.\n\n\n: Am, G, F\n(Am)Raj ke rulaaya\n\n(Am)Raj ke hasaya\n\n(F)Maine dil kho ke (Am)ishq kamaaya\n\n(Am)Maanga jo usne (F)ek sitaara\n\n(G)Humne zameen pe (F)chaand bulaaya\n(Am)Jo aankhon se… haye\n\n(Am)Wo jo aankhon se ikk pal naa (F)ojhal hue\n\n(Am)Wo jo aankhon se ikk pal naa (F)ojhal hue\n\n(G)Laapta ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n(Am)Sochta hu…\n\n(Am)Sochta hoon ke woh kitne (F)maasum the\n\n(Am)Sochta hoon ke woh kitne (F)maasum the\n\n(G)Kya se kya ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(Am)Sochta hu ke wo kitne (F)maasoom the\n\n(G)Kya se kya ho gye (Em/Am)dekhtey (F)dekhtey\n(Am)Sochta hoon ke woh kitne (F)maasoom the\n\n(Am)Sochta hoon ke woh kitne (F)maasoom the\n\n(G)Kya se kya ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (F)dekhte\n(Am)Woh jo kehte the beechdenge na (F)hum kabhi\n\n(Am)Woh jo kehte the beechdenge na (F)hum kabhi\n\n(G)Alvida ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(Am)Sochta hoon…\n(Am)Aate jaate the jo (F)saans ban kar kabhi\n\n(Am)Aate jaate the jo (F)saans ban kar kabhi\n\n(G)Wo hawa ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(G)Wo hawa ho gye… haye…\n\nOh… ho ho…\n\nOh… ho ho…\n(G)Wo hawa ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(G)Alvida ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(G)Lapata ho gye (Em/Am)dekhte (Am)dekhte\n\n(G)Kya se kya ho gaye (Em