 thing that helps us survive and battle with life gracefully. Kar har maidaan fateh from the film Sanju is the perfect example of the above statements. Sung by the mellifluous Sukhwinder Singh and the melodious Shreya Ghoshal, this track has been composed by the versatile Vikram Montrose and has been penned down by the poetic Shekhar Astitwa. From the feature film soundtrack genre, this melody uses the guitars, the violins, live percussions and drums quite euphoniously. Kar har maidan fateh chords are simple and easy. The guitar chords of Kar har maidaan fateh are C#m, E, A, B, Gb. The melody has been played in the C#m scale with a moderately paced tempo and a signature 4/4 beat. The chords of Kar har maidaan fateh follow the strumming pattern of D UUD UUD.\n \n: D UUD UUD\nD – Down Strum\n\nU – Up Strum\n: C#m/Dbm\n\n\n: 86\n\n\n: 4/4\n\n\n: C#m, E, A, B, G#m\n: C#m\n(C#m)Pighla de zanjeerein\n\n(C#m)Bana unki shamsheerein\n(C#m)Kar har maidaan fateh o bandeya\n\n(C#m)Kar har maidan fateh\n(C#m)Ghayal parinda hai tu\n\n(C#m)Dikhla de zinda hai tu\n\n(C#m)Baaqi hai tujhme hausla\n\n(C#m)Tere junoon ke aage\n\n(C#m)Ambar panaahe maange\n\n(C#m)Kar daale tu jo faisla\n(C#m)Roothi taqdeerein toh kya\n\n(C#m)Tooti shamsheerein toh kya\n\n(C#m)Tooti shamsheeron se hi ho…\nKar(C#m) har maidaan (E)fateh\n\nKar (C#m)har maidaan (A)fat(B)eh\n\nKar(C#m) har maidan(E) fateh re bandeya\n\nHar maidaan(A) fat(B)eh (x2)\n: C#m, E, Gb, A, B\n(C#m)In gardishon ke baadalon pe chadh ke\n\n(A)Waqt ka girabaan pakad ke\n\n(E)Puchna hai jeet ka pata\n\n(G#m)Jeet ka pata\n(C#m)Inn mutthiyon mein chand taare bhar ke\n\n(A)Aasmaan ki hadh se guzar ke\n\n(E)Ho ja tu bheed se juda\n\n(G#m)Bheed se juda\n\n(C#m)Bheed se juda\n(C#m)Kehne ko zarra hai tu\n\n(B)Loha ka charra hai tu\n\n(Gb)Tooti shamsheeron se hi (A)ho\nKar(C#m) har maidan (E)fateh\n\nKar (C#m)har maidan (A)fat(B)eh\n\nKar(C#m) har maidan(E) fateh re bandeya\n\nHar maidaan(A) fat(B)eh (x3)\n: C#m, E, A, B (x4)\nTeri (C#m)koshishe