INSERT INTO `pages_ccat_question` VALUES (1,1,'Which of the following correctly shows the hierarchy of arithmetic operations in C?','D\r\nSimply called as BODMAS (Bracket of Division, Multiplication, Addition and Subtraction).\r\n\r\nHow Do I Remember ? BODMAS !\r\n\r\nB - Brackets first\r\nO - Orders (ie Powers and Square Roots, etc.)\r\nDM - Division and Multiplication (left-to-right)\r\nAS - Addition and Subtraction (left-to-right)','/ + * -','* - / +','+ - / *','/ * + -','Yes'),(2,2,'Which of the following special symbol allowed in a variable name?','D\r\nVariable names in C are made up of letters (upper and lower case) and digits. The underscore character (\"_\") is also permitted. Names must not begin with a digit.','* (asterisk)','| (pipeline)','- (hyphen)','_ (underscore)','Yes'),(3,3,'How would you round off a value from 1.66 to 2.0?','A\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n#include<math.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , ceil(1.44) );\r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , ceil(1.66) );\r\n \r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , floor(1.44) );    \r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , floor(1.66) );\r\n\r\n    return 0;\r\n}\r\n// Output:\r\n// Result : 2.000000\r\n// Result : 2.000000\r\n// Result : 1.000000\r\n// Result : 1.000000','ceil(1.66)','floor(1.66)','roundup(1.66)','roundto(1.66)','Yes'),(4,3,'How would you round off a value from 1.66 to 2.0?','A\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n#include<math.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , ceil(1.44) );\r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , ceil(1.66) );\r\n \r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , floor(1.44) );    \r\n    printf(\"\\n Result : %f\" , floor(1.66) );\r\n\r\n    return 0;\r\n}\r\n// Output:\r\n// Result : 2.000000\r\n// Result : 2.000000\r\n// Result : 1.000000\r\n// Result : 1.000000','ceil(1.66)','floor(1.66)','roundup(1.66)','roundto(1.66)','Yes'),(5,5,'Which of the following are unary operators in C?','An operation with only one operand is called unary operation.\r\n Unary operators:\r\n! Logical NOT operator.\r\n~ bitwise NOT operator.\r\nsizeof Size-of operator.\r\n&& Logical AND is a logical operator.\r\n\r\nTherefore, 1, 2, 3 are unary operators.','!','sizeOf','~','&&','Yes'),(6,6,'In which order do the following gets evaluated','2. Arithmetic operators: *, /, %, +, -\r\n1. Relational operators: >, <, >=, <=, ==, !=\r\n3. Logical operators : !, &&, ||\r\n4. Assignment operators: =','Relational','Arithmetic','Logical','Assignment','Yes'),(7,7,'The keyword used to transfer control from a function back to the calling function is','The keyword return is used to transfer control from a function back to the calling function.','return','goto','switch','back','Yes'),(8,8,'How many times the program will print \"ccatcracker\" ?\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    printf(\"IndiaBIX\");\r\n    main();\r\n    return 0;\r\n}','B\r\n\r\nA call stack or function stack is used for several related purposes, but the main reason for having one is to keep track of the point to which each active subroutine should return control when it finishes executing.\r\n\r\nA stack overflow occurs when too much memory is used on the call stack.\r\n\r\nHere function main() is called repeatedly and its return address is stored in the stack. After stack memory is full. It shows stack overflow error.','Infinite times','Till stack overflows','65535 times','32767 times','Yes'),(9,9,'What will be the output of the program in 16 bit platform (Turbo C under DOS)?\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    int fun();\r\n    int i;\r\n    i = fun();\r\n    printf(\"%d\\n\", i);\r\n    return 0;\r\n}\r\nint fun()\r\n{\r\n    _AX = 1990;\r\n}','C \r\n\r\nTurbo C (Windows): The return value of the function is taken from the Accumulator _AX=1990.\r\n\r\nBut it may not work as expected in GCC compiler (Linux).','Garbage value','0 (Zero)','1990','No output','Yes'),(10,10,'What is (void*)0?','A\r\n\r\nSince void pointer can return any type of pointer, in this problem it returns an integer pointer. Since 0 is null value of integer, the pointer return will be a null pointer....','NULL Pointer','void pointer','Error','None','Yes'),(11,11,'In which header file is the NULL macro defined?','D\r\nThe macro \"NULL\" is defined in locale.h, stddef.h, stdio.h, stdlib.h, string.h, time.h, and wchar.h.','stdio.h','math.h','stddef.h','stdio.h and stddef.h','Yes'),(12,12,'If a variable is a pointer to a structure, then which of the following operator is used to access data members of the structure through the pointer variable?','A\r\n\r\nPointer is just the address value, where the variable is stored. To get the address value we use \"->\" its just an representation','->','.','*','&','Yes'),(13,13,'What will be the output of the program ?\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    int x=30, *y, *z;\r\n    y=&x; /* Assume address of x is 500 and integer is 4 byte size */\r\n    z=y;\r\n    *y++=*z++;\r\n    x++;\r\n    printf(\"x=%d, y=%d, z=%d\\n\", x, y, z);\r\n    return 0;\r\n}','A\r\n\r\nAs x=30; y=z= 500;\r\n\r\n*z++=504= *y++;\r\n\r\nx++=31;\r\n\r\nSo the answer is 31, 504, 504.','x=31, y=504, z=504','x=31, y=502, z=502','x=31, y=502, z=502','x=31, y=498, z=498','Yes'),(14,14,'What will be the output of the program ?\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    int i=3, *j, k;\r\n    j = &i;\r\n    printf(\"%d\\n\", i**j*i+*j);\r\n    return 0;\r\n}','D\r\n\r\ni**j*i+*j\r\n\r\nHere the * symol before j is pointer value of j and * symbol before i and after i is for multiplication.\r\n\r\nSo the execution will be\r\n\r\ni**J = 3*3 = 9\r\n\r\ni**j*i = 9*3 = 27\r\n\r\ni**j*i+*j = 27+3 = 30.','29','28','25','30','Yes'),(15,15,'What will be the output of the program ?\r\n\r\n#include<stdio.h>\r\n\r\nint main()\r\n{\r\n    char str[20] = \"Hello\";\r\n    char *const p=str;\r\n    *p=\'M\';\r\n    printf(\"%s\\n\", str);\r\n    return 0;\r\n}','B\r\n\r\nAs p is const variable pointer it canno